title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and dice apples, set aside.
Put oil in mixing bowl. Add sugar and egg, beat until creamy.
Add small amount of flour to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Batter will become very stiff.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Spread evenly in bottom of large square pan or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Cool 15 minutes removing from the pan.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Pour oil into one, vanilla into another, and vinegar into the third one.
Pour cold water over all and stir to mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Peel and slice the potatoes. In bowl mix soup with 1/2 can water.
Layer potatoes, hamburger, soup and cheese with 2 layers each always ending with cheese. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes; the last 15 minutes of baking, remove cover.
Will feed 8 to 10.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Soak beans covered with water overnight.
Add onion, sugar, salt and bacon (slightly cooked).
Stir from time to time.
Cook slow or in crock-pot for 6 hours.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Trim crusts from white bread and spread one side of each slice with butter.
Arrange bread, buttered side down, in a baking dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over bread slices, then sprinkle Jack cheese over.
Distribute chilies over mixture.
These should be minced and seeds removed.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, paprika, salt, garlic powder, oregano, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes until lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
I sometimes lay strips of foil around the outer edges if they get too brown before the center.

title: hearty hungarian goulash
directions: In large saucepan heat oil and brown meat.
Add onion soup mix and paprika blended with tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in flour and salt blended with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes. Cook noodles according to package directions.
To serve, arrange goulash over noodles and garnish with parsley.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: gingambo with codfish
directions: Boil codfish for one hour and pour out water.
Let is sit in a fresh water for 12 hours.
Pour olive oil into a pot with 1/4 cup of water.
Add okra, pepper and onions.
Let it cook in vapor for 20 minutes and add codfish.
Let cook for another 15 minutes or until onions and peppers are well cooked.

title: company stew
directions: Combine soups, wine and meat and cook in 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Peel and cut vegetables into large chunks; cook until just tender.
After the meat is done, arrange the vegetables into large shallow pan or big ovenproof platter.
Spoon hot meat mixture over the vegetables.
Spread green beans on top and lightly blend all together; a small amount of water can be added.
Cover and return to oven for nearly 30 minutes until piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs. Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Blend in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain well. Mix all ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: strawberry topping for angel food cake
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar and salt, then add strawberries and mix well.
Refrigerate until jelled enough to spread.
Cut cake into two layers.
Spread one-half of jello mixture on bottom layer and cover with Cool Whip. Place top layer of cake on this.
Spread remaining jello and cover with Cool Whip.
Also spread Cool Whip around sides of cake. Refrigerate before cutting.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix and heat, uncovered, for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy cherry tart
directions: Spread cherries in an 8-inch cake pan.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix.
Should be a crumbly mix.
Sprinkle on top of cherries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce, litchi nuts and almonds.
Line a large clear bowl with lettuce (or make up individual bowls).
Spoon salad ingredients over lettuce and top with almonds and lithci nuts.
Serves 12.
Makes a very large salad to serve a group.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
In a large pot or crockpot, place all of the ingredients, except the Fritos and cheese.
Cook for 1 hour.
Top each individual bowl of soup with Fritos and cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put hamburger in casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Then cut up onion; put over hamburger.	Mix can of cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can of water together, then pour over.	Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger-cheese bake
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in skillet; stir in next 5 ingredients.
Cook noodles using package directions; drain. Combine remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Mix well. Layer half the noodles, half the ground beef mixture and all the cottage cheese mixture in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Add remaining noodles and ground beef mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes; stir now and then.
Uncover and cook until sauce thickens.

title: catherine's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then add to creamed ingredients.
Combine sour cream and vanilla, then mix all ingredients together well.

title: potato skins
directions: Wash and scrub skins of medium sized potatoes.
Bake in oven or microwave until tender but not mushy.
Quarter each potato, cutting lengthwise, then carefully remove all but about 1/4-inch of the potato, leaving the skin intact.
Place skins on baking tray or cookie sheet.
Brush skins with melted margarine; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Return skins to oven until cheese melts.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda and oatmeal (nuts if desired).
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes for crispy cookies, 5 to 7 minutes for chewy cookies.

title: brownie's squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and cut up into pieces.
Boil until tender. Drain.
Mash with potato masher (not to mushy).
Add margarine, chopped onion, sugar, cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into a greased deep casserole dish.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice squares
directions: Saute onion and mix with remaining ingredients.
Microwave on Medium for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mary's award winning chili
directions: Brown beef in olive oil. Add onion, pepper and garlic, stirring frequently. Add seasonings, ketchup and water. Add brown sugar and vinegar. Taste (add salt and pepper, if necessary, or more Tabasco sauce).
Simmer for 1 hour, then add beans and heat through.
Serve over rice. Garnish with shredded cheese.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Beat together the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add melted chocolate and margarine; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then turn oven to 250° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Cool completely.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan; cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
May use any vegetables; corn is good.
May also use chili pepper, paprika, dash of cinnamon or garlic flakes in addition to salt and pepper.

title: simple black forest cake
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
Bake according to directions for cake mix.

title: dad's sauerkraut
directions: Rinsed sauerkraut, cook, simmer sauerkraut, garlic and caraway seed 1/2 hour to 1 hour.
After cooking, put in bacon and bacon grease and pour over the sauerkraut.
Serve warm. You may add sliced kielbasa.

title: cranberry-raspberry salad
directions: In a large bowl pour boiling water over gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Chill until very thick, but not set.
With a rotary beater, beat in sour cream and cranberry sauce.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: english apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Stir
in flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and water.
Mix until smooth. Stir in pecans. Set aside.

title: chile con klingon
directions: Brown meat; add pepper and onions.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and beans; stir.
Add chili powder, salt and red pepper.
Cover and cook over low flame for approximately 45 minutes.
The longer it simmers, the better the taste.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and toss.
Serves 6.

title: divinity
directions: Cook all ingredients, except vanilla, nuts and egg whites, to soft ball stage when dropped in water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add boiled mixture; beat until glaze changes.
Add vanilla and nuts; drop onto waxed paper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Drain beans and mix beans, soup, garlic cheese and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove and add onions on top and cook for about 6 more minutes.

title: topping for salmon or halibut
directions: Mix together.
Spread over fish fillet.
Bake at 350° until fish is done.

title: party bread
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Saut onions in butter.
Add corn, sour cream and cheese to onions.
Spread mixture over corn bread batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm.
Leftover ham or green chilies may be added to batter.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Stir soup to make a creamy consistency.
Add milk, cheese, onion, uncooked macaroni and dried beef.
Fold in eggs.

title: graham pie crust mix
directions: In a food processor or bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and cinnamon; pulse or cut in butter until mixture begins to clump together.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 months.
Yield:
about 7 1/2 cups mix (4 pie crusts).

title: baked pork chops and vegetables
directions: Brown chops in fat in heavy skillet.
Remove chops and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Wash rice and add.
Saute onion and green pepper slowly for about 5 minutes in remaining fat in skillet.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and simmer until sauce is thick.
Pour over rice and chops and cook in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes or until meat is thoroughly cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Melt chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Gradually add 3 cups milk, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Combine remaining milk and cornstarch; stir well.
Add to saucepan.
Cook 30 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently. Cook 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yield:
8 servings (about 167 calories per 1/2-cup).

title: bean bread
directions: Mix corn meal and soda with boiling water to spread stage. Add beans.
Stir good.
Bake in hot oven.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Beat applesauce, sugar and flour.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° until set.
Top with meringue.

title: carrot souffle(large quantity recipe)
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots; remove from heat and drain. Process in a food processor till smooth. Beat eggs and set aside. Mix carrots with remaining ingredients; slowly add beaten eggs. Mix until well blended. Pour into a 12 x 18 baking pan sprayed with Pam. Bake for 1 hour or until center is set at 350°. If using convection oven, reduce heat to between 300° and 325°. Check often so that it doesn't brown too quickly. Serves 30 good size servings.

title: blackberry pecan cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat for 5 minutes at low speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake comes away from sides of pan. Cool.
Ice with Blackberry Frosting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and ham.
Put to the side. Work cream cheese well. Add onions, ham and garlic salt.
Mix real well. The block cheese will make a ball better.
Mold the mixture into a ball and refrigerate.
Serve as a snack or appetizer with crackers or chips.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender; let cool until you can work it with your hands.
Mix with butter and confectioners sugar until it forms a dough.
Spread a cup of sugar and roll out; put peanut butter on top of dough and roll.
When chilled, slice.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil & beaten eggs.
Add 2 Tbsp. poppy seed in the boiling water, then add to cake mix.
Put into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Debone broiled chicken and put in bottom of casserole dish. Cut corn tortillas into long strips and layer on top of chicken. Sprinkle onions on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle grated cheese next. Mix in a separate bowl chicken broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour this mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and beat well.
Pour batter into prepared cake pans (2 layer pan or one 13 x 9-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool and ice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter-sugar mixture. Mix flour, plus baking powder, into butter mix alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
This is too hot in my oven; I use 325°.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, oregano and garlic salt.
Add cooked spaghetti and spaghetti sauce.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and then cottage cheese.
Place remaining meat mixture on cottage cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese.
Spread over crust.
Spoon hot meat over mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned hot cocoa(microwaved)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together into fine even mixture in microsafe cup.
Add 3 tablespoons of the milk.
Mix well.
Heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Remove and stir well.
Add remaining milk and stir well.
Heat in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and stir again.
If not hot enough, return to microwave for a few more seconds.
Add marshmallow if desired.

title: center cut ham with apricots for the microwave
directions: Score edges of ham slices; place in 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) baking dish.
Combine apricot juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and nutmeg in a small mixing bowl and pour over ham.
Top with apricots and dot with butter.
Microwave on Roast for 20 to 25 minutes or until ham is hot and sauce thickened.
Let stand for five minutes before serving.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown beef, bell pepper, garlic, onion and celery.
Add rest of ingredients.
Steam slowly 10 minutes.
Put in casserole, bake 40 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix; divide in half and roll between wax paper.
Makes two pie crusts.

title: hawaiian lemon pie
directions: Combine pineapple, brown sugar, coconut and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Spread over bottom of pastry shell.
Cover edge of shell with foil.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, removing foil after first 5 minutes.
Meanwhile in saucepan, combine pudding mix with 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in water and egg yolks. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and remaining butter.
Cover with clear plastic wrap; cool, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg whites on high speed to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in remaining sugar to stiff peaks.
Fold white into cooled filing.
Pile in shell.
Chill at least 4 hours. Garnish with toasted coconut, if desired.

title: fluffy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl. Beat with mixer on medium speed until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hrs. or until set. Top with whatever you like.

title: quick potato soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, put raw potatoes and onions in water. Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Slightly mash potatoes with a fork to thicken the soup.
Add milk, butter, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat but do not boil.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in a large bowl.
Next, mix sugar, water, light corn syrup, salt and butter in a small cooking pot.
This should be cooked slowly over a low heat.
You will need to test it occasionally.
This can be done by dropping a small bit of the mixture into cold water.
If mixture is ready, it will form a hard ball when it is dropped into the cold water.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add ground beef; stir until brown.
Add tomato sauce and water; stir well.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, parsley flakes and noodles.
Cook for about 12 minutes, or until water is absorbed and noodles are tender.
Add peas; cook 5 more minutes.
Pour into casserole and serve.
If desired, casserole may be topped with mounds of mashed potatoes and browned in oven or under broiler.

title: fresh berry salad
directions: Pick over berries for best ones; rinse and dry.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Place cheese and bacon on top. Mix eggs, milk, parsley and seasoning; pour over bread, etc. Melt oleo and drizzle over top. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: holiday dump cake
directions: To
long
cake
pan, pour in pineapple, then cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle
cake mix on top.
Pour margarine over cake mix.
Add pecans on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: onion dill bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place first four ingredients in order given.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and heat just until warm (do not boil).
Pour into bread pan.
Select "white bread" setting.
Bake according to bread machine directions.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add dressing.

title: griddle cakes with apples
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Add dissolved yeast in warm milk.
Mix one egg, sugar and a pinch of salt.
Cover; let stand in warm place to rise.
Mix in pared and diced apples.
Allow to rise until double in bulk.
Drop batter by spoonfuls on a hot griddle or pan and fry both sides to a nice brown.
When serving, spread with jam or honey.

title: pork chop casserole(serves 6)
directions: Layer a 9 x 11-inch baking dish with peeled, sliced potatoes and onions, thinly sliced, alternating layers.
Cover with soup and milk mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, lemon juice, rind and salt in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar melts and mixture slightly thickens.
Cool.
Fold in whip cream and egg whites.
Line pan with most of crumbs.
Pour in mixture and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Freeze at coldest temperature.

title: chinese tacos
directions: Marinate beef in soy, sherry and cornstarch at least 30 minutes. Wash, drain and dry lettuce leaves large enough to wrap ingredients in.
Prepare vegetables for stir frying and mix with spices.
Fry in hot oil and drain.
Fry beef in hot oil and drain. Mix with vegetables.
Cook rice sticks in 1-inch hot oil; use 2 1/2 cups rice sticks at a time.
As soon as they puff, turn, remove and drain (they will cook fast).
On each lettuce leaf, put a nest of rice sticks, meat and vegetables, soy or hot sauce, if desired, then wrap and eat.
Have lots of napkins.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make well in center of bowl. Pour oil and buttermilk in well.
Do not mix.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (extra good).
Pour in well.
Stir in circular motion, then knead with fingers for about 1 minute.
Place in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Pinch off as needed.
Do not let rise.
Roll each piece in a ball and make into biscuits.
Place in an ungreased pan and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: grandma's rice
directions: In large skillet, saute onions and butter until yellow.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, bouillon cube and rice.
Cook 20 minutes on low heat or until rice is cooked.
Remove from heat and add coconut and nuts.
This is great as a side dish or can be used as a stuffing for chicken.

title: pumpkin stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat in 2 tablespoons of oil. Add water, potatoes, carrots, green peppers, garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 2 hours. Stir in bouillon and tomatoes. Wash the pumpkin, remove the top and set aside. Discard seeds and loose fibers from inside. Place pumpkin in a shallow, sturdy baking pan. Spoon stew into pumpkin and replace the top. Brush the outside of the pumpkin with the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil. Bake at 325° for 2 hours or just until the pumpkin is tender. Do not overbake. Serve stew from the pumpkin, scooping out a little pumpkin with each serving. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, cheese, soup, salad dressing, onion and pepper.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle combined crushed corn flakes and margarine over all. Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: tammy's seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill before serving. Taste great for all boiled seafood!

title: wampki
directions: Boil cabbage soft enough to roll.
Mix ground beef, pork sausage and onion soup mix.
Roll meat mixture into cabbage leaves.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream and milk.
Mix in meat thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: clams casino
directions: Steam clams.
Remove clams from shell, then put in 1/2 of shell loose.
Brown bacon; drain and crumble when cool.
Chop pimento, onion and green pepper.
Add bacon to this.
Put 1 drop of lemon juice and 1 drop of Tabasco sauce on each clam.
Top each clam with bacon/vegetable mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream buttter with sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Fold in chopped blanched almonds, figs and raisins.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes until golden brown and cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serve drizzled with Burnt Sugar Syrup and decorated with almonds.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place tortilla shells on bottom of pan until covered.
Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and prepare as package directs.
Add refried beans; spread over shells.
Spread with sour cream (optional).
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onions. Top with another layer of shells.
Mix gravy and enchilada sauce and pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: savannah chocolate cake with hot fudge sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the brown sugar with the shortening with an electric mixer.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla then the melted chocolate.
With the mixer running, add eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift the flour with the baking soda and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the sugar mixture and beat for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 13 by 9 by 2 inch cake pan.
Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake until the cake is springy and a toothpick can be inserted and removed cleanly, about 40 minutes.
Allow cake to cool for 10 minutes then turn it out onto a rack to finish cooling.

title: egg-stra special breakfast
directions: Pat hash browns into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Brown sausage and onion and put over hash browns.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg, parsley and pour over.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt the cheese in a double boiler.
Place pimentos and sour cream in a bowl. As soon as the cheese has melted, mix the cheese with the pimentos and sour cream.
Dip can be served warm or cold.

title: aunt vickie's apple dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together cream cheese, marshmallow cream and cinnamon.
Blend until creamed.
Dip sliced apples into mixture and enjoy!

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Do not peel.
Cut each apple into eight wedges.
Arrange wedges in a circle in 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, sugar and walnuts.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven until tender and crisp and apples hold their shape, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot topped with ice cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into a large pan to make crust.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef and drain. Put in crock-pot. Combine all the other ingredients and pour into crock-pot. Cook on low for 10 hours.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except mayonnaise real well.
Stir in mayonnaise and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased baking dish. Cover with crushed corn flakes or cracker crumbs and dot with small pieces of margarine.
Bake at 350°.

title: fiery deep fried coconut shrimp
directions: Combine eggs, cayenne and seasoning salt in shallow pan. Place flour in another shallow pan.
Combine bread crumbs and coconut in third pan.
Dredge shrimp in flour, shaking off excess.
Holding shrimp by tail, dip into eggs.
Roll shrimp in bread crumb mixture, coating thoroughly.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add oil, garlic, onions, green pepper and other spices except chili powder.
Add these ingredients to a large pot after steaming in a skillet.
Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste and chili powder.
Stir in beans, cloves and bay leaves (drain kidney bean juice).
Cook at least 1 hour; the longer it cooks, the better it is.

title: teen town fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, Milnot and marshmallow cream in heavy saucepan.
Heat slowly to boiling.
Stir frequently when mixture boils (so boiling cannot be stopped by stirring).
Time 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cook onions and garlic in butter in large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 4 minutes. Add lemon juice and the next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Serve over fettucini.
Sprinkle with parsley. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce. Place chicken, skin side down (you can also use skinless chicken), in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish (sprayed with Pam).
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Baste during cooking. Pour remaining sauce over chicken prior to baking.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until crust browns.
Turn oven to 300° and continue cooking until knife inserted in filling comes out clean.

title: ellie's date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soak.
When cool, beat well. Add sugar, egg and shortening to date mixture.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite-size pieces and mix with broccoli and onion.
Mix vinegar, sugar, oil and mayonnaise.
Pour over cauliflower and broccoli and let stand overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit to make 2 cups juice.
Cook juices in pudding. Cool.
Mix with fruit.
Slice bananas and mix with fruit and pudding.
Chill.

title: tuna seafood patties
directions: Mix drained tuna, dressing, mustard, vegetables, pimento, seasonings and 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs.
Shape mixture into 15 (2-inch) balls.
Roll in remaining 3/4 cup bread crumbs, coating well.
Flatten balls into small patties.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add tuna patties.
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown, adding additional oil, as needed.
Remove from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, bone and cut into small pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup (undiluted), chicken broth and mixed vegetables (cooked as directed).
Mix and place in baking dish.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread margarine on bread.
Place in hot skillet.
Put slice of cheese on each slice of bread, then the rest of ingredients. Once hot, remove from skillet.
Makes one sandwich.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover with dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt half of butter in 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients together except butter.
Pour into casserole dish. Slice remaining butter in pats and place on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: ciambellono(italian pound cake)
directions: Beat together until creamy the eggs, Crisco, sugar, and flavoring.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Continue beating until mixed well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender and save broth.
Debone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Melt butter and toss with cracker crumbs.
Layer half of cracker mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place all of the chicken on top.
Mix sour cream, soup and broth well.
Pour over chicken and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until brown on top, at 350°.

title: hamburger taco casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Drain tomatoes (reserving liquid) and add tomatoes to browned meat.
Pour rice on top, adding reserved tomato juice and enough water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add taco seasoning; stir and cover.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top when ready.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sour cream, Cheddar cheese and soup; mix in hash browns and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for an hour at 350°.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: microwave peanuts
directions: Place nuts in a single layer in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.

Microwave raw peanuts on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes. Drizzle with cooking oil and sprinkle with seasoned salt. Microwave for an additional 45 seconds to 1 minute on High (100%) or until golden brown.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients except Parmesan cheese and cooked pasta.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and refrigerate overnight.
Reheat.
Add pasta and cheese.

title: nondairy chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 wells in the flour mixture.
In one well, pour vinegar, the other vanilla and the third well, put oil.
Then pour 2 cups cold water over this.
Mix with portable mixer right in the pan.
Be sure to scrape sides and bottom while mixing.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Mix together oil and sugar in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add beaten egg yolks and hot water; mix until blended.
Add pumpkin.
Gradually fold in sifted dry ingredients; add nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into a 9-inch tube which has been greased and floured.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Cool and ice with your favorite icing.

title: banana bread
directions: Peel and mash bananas.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream. Add eggs one at a time, then bananas, then sifted flour with cooking soda.
Add almond flavoring last.
Mix thoroughly but do not overbeat.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. Stores well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into lightly greased tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice #2
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rice, soups, milk, mushrooms and melted butter.
Pour mixture into greased dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over all.
Ccover tightly with foil.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 320° to 325°.

title: barbecue beans
directions: In a Dutch oven cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
In a colander, drain one can of the pork and beans, kidney beans, read beans and lima beans.
Place in the Dutch oven all the beans, the bacon, the barbecue sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 24.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix together other ingredients.
Add to dry mixture; stir carefully.
Pour batter in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pans.
Turn out onto cooling racks.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: breakfast sundaes(a delightful enhancement of boring dry cereal)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a soup bowl (of ample capacity), allowing your creativity to have full reign.
Microwave on High for approximately 40 seconds.
This warms fruit and turns ice cream to soft serve.

title: speedy southwest spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti (al dente); whisk milk and egg and add to hot pasta.
Spread in greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook meat (while spaghetti is cooking) with onion and green pepper; add spices, cook 2 minutes.
Spread on pasta.
Top with shredded cheeses.
Bake in lower 1/3 of oven 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Measure flour, soda, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Cream shortening and peanut butter with brown and granulated sugars until fluffy in a large bowl; beat in egg.
Sift in flour mixture, adding alternately with orange juice and blending well to make a stiff dough.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough, a teaspoonful at a time into balls; place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten, crisscross fashion with a fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until golden.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely on wire racks.
(I like to use extra crunchy peanut butter in them.)

title: mom's yankee pot roast
directions: In hot bacon fat in 6-quart ovenproof Dutch oven, brown meat, turning with 2 wooden spoons until well browned on all sides, about 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put roast to one side of pan; add onion, carrot, garlic, bay leaf; saute 5 minutes.
Add water to beef broth to make 1 1/2 cups; pour over meat, along with tomato sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost fork-tender; add boiling onions.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Remove roast and onions to warm platter.
Strain pan liquids.
In small bowl, combine flour and 1/2 cup water, stirring until smooth.
Return strained liquid to Dutch oven; stir in flour mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over meat.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Place all ingredients on aluminum foil.
Seal well.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.
Each dinner should be individually wrapped if making more than one.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Bake at 250 for 5 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add milk and corn; mix well again.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk; stir in chicken, egg and peas.
Top with chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in tightly closed jar. Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat, until real dark, in oil, then remove meat to a boil.
Saute onion and garlic in same oil until tender.
Add back the meat and add water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, then add barley, potatoes and the beef bouillon.
Cook until potatoes and barley are tender.

title: creamy double-decker fudge
directions: In a 2 cup glass measuring cup with handle, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup Eagle Brand milk; cook on High in microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
In 2 cup glass measuring cup, combine remaining Eagle Brand milk and chocolate chips; repeat preceding procedure.
Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; spread evenly on peanut butter layer.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: fast fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Stir well.
Melt margarine or butter in a pan or baking dish.
Pour batter in margarine and add fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: With electric mixer, beat the cream cheese. Add powdered sugar, extracts and heavy cream.
Beat until smooth. Pour in pie shell and refrigerate until firm, about 8 to 10 hours. Garnish with strawberries.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored. Add milk and vanilla, then beat in dry ingredients until batter is fairly smooth.
Run batter into hot oil, using a slow wide circular motion and maintaining as steady a stream as possible.
Fry, turning once, until golden brown, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Dust generously with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 large cakes.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl and mix well.
Whisk eggs in a large bowl until blended.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla extract and lemon zest and mix well.
Stir the dry ingredients into egg mixture until blended.
Chill, covered, for 30 minutes or longer.
Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
Drop the cookie dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Mist the bottom of a 3 inch flat bottom glass with water and dip glass in additional sugar.
Press the top of each cookie lightly with the glass to flatten, misting glass with water and dipping in sugar before pressing each cookie.
Bake cookies until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Store in airtight containers or freeze for future use.

title: tomato jello
directions: Make jello according to package.
When slightly thick, add stewed tomatoes.
Let set.
Tastes better second day.

title: almond skorpor
directions: Make into 3 loaves crosswise on a cookie sheet (greased). Brush with egg on top and sprinkle with almonds on top.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until a little brown.
Cool and cut into slices.
Put back on cookie sheet, reduce oven to 200°.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Cook rhubarb, cornstarch, water and salt until thick. Add vanilla. Cool. Combine flour, oatmeal. brown sugar and soda. Cut in shortening. Add nuts to flour mixture. Put 3/4 of flour mixture in bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Pour cooled rhubarb mixture over crust mixture. Sprinkle with remaining flour mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon garlic brussels sprouts and carrots
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add Brussels sprouts, carrots, garlic, basil and pepper.
Saute about 7 minutes until tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in lemon juice; cook about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings, 2/3 cup each.

title: currant jelly(this recipe takes some time.)
directions: Wash fruit and mash.
Place in saucepan.
Add water and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Place in jelly bag (similar to a cheesecloth that allows liquid to drain through) and let drain several hours.
Do not squeeze.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together chopped onion, soups, mayonnaise and cheese.
In baking dish, place the chicken and broccoli in layers.
Between each layer, spread the mixture of soups, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Put stuffing on top and pour melted margarine over top of dressing.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Very tasty!
Fills an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: pear honey
directions: Grind pears and apples.
Measure and add 1 cup of sugar to each cup of pulp.
Cook for about 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Serve with fresh vegetables or chunks of rye bread.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Use medium size mixing bowl. Pour the meal into the bowl. Stir in enough boiling water to mix well but in a patting consistency. Scoop about 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture in hand (carefully, as this is hot!).
Pat out into a pancake like patty.
Cook on top
of stove in hot skillet covered with about 1/4-inch of shortening or oil. Brown on both sides.
I like mine slightly crispy.
Serve with butter, jelly or syrup.
Makes about 8 patties.

title: iced mocha mint coffee
directions: Brew tea as usual, but instead of adding sugar or honey to sweeten, stir a teaspoon or two of fruit preserves into the cup. Strawberry, cherry and apricot are especially good.

title: mom's chili
directions: Simmer hamburger, onion and garlic in a little oil until done and drain off liquid.
Blend tomatoes (in blender), then add to hamburger mixture.
Add chili mix, chili pepper, pinto beans and approximately 1 cup water.
The chili will appear thin until allowed to cook for some time.
Simmer on very low heat for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt as desired.
Best if let simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheese 'n' v-8 muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Combine wet and dry mixtures; fold together.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Put into 2 greased loaf pans or a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° about 45 to 55 minutes. Squeeze juice from 2 lemons and mix with 1/4 cup powdered sugar. Pour over warm bread.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add and mix well.
Cream together.
Drop small balls on cookie sheets.
Press with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips and brown in butter. Remove.
Brown chopped onion and mushrooms.
Return meat to skillet.
Add chicken soup, sour cream and cottage cheese. Add 1 can beef broth. Cook slowly for 1 hour.
If desired, thicken with cornstarch.

title: coconut joys
directions: Combine confectioners sugar and coconut in bowl; toss to mix. Add butter; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Make indentation in each ball.
Fill with melted chocolate.
Chill until firm. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: In a glass casserole dish sprayed with Pam, place thawed vegetables.
Add cut slices of Velveeta cheese over vegetables, then spread crushed crackers over top and drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split
directions: Combine powdered sugar, softened butter and eggs.
Beat 20 minutes, no less, without stopping.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Put bread in casserole.
Cover with cooked sausage, then cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, cream and seasonings. Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle mushrooms on top.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 1 1/2 hours.
Take out of refrigerator at least one hour before cooking.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: helen's chicken breasts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put chicken in Ziploc bags.
Cover with mixture and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
One and one-half hours before baking, remove from refrigerator.
Roll up chicken into rolls, then roll in bread crumbs.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Good hot or cold!

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Combine in mixer the butter, sugars, eggs, vanilla and pudding.
Blend well.
Pour into large bowl.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll out and press.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: microwave cranberry carrots(total cooking time:  13 to 14 minutes)
directions: Cook carrots according to package.
Place butter in 1 1/2 to 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook, covered, on High (Max power) for 1 minute, or until cranberry sauce is melted.
Stir and mix in cooked carrots.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: christmas scent(not edible)
directions: Put peelings and spices into 2 quarts water.
Bring to boil. Simmer all day.
Can be place in refrigerator.
Water added and simmer again.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs
well
in
large
bowl
or
2-quart measuring pitcher, with
a
pouring
spout.
(This
is
important.)
Mix sugar, flour and
salt together and add to eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Place
pie
shell
on
oven
rack
before pouring in custard.
(This will fill a 9 or 10-inch pie shell too full to transfer from counter to oven.) Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top.
Bake at
375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until knife comes out clean from center.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased pie dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange jello and boiling water or boil the pineapple juice instead of the water.
Add pineapple and let cool.
Next add sharp shredded cheese to jello mixture.
Then fold in Dream Whip.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Prepare macaroni as label directs.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.

In a large bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper. Stuff rounded tablespoonful of cheese mixture into each cooked shell. Spoon 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce into each of two greased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Arrange stuffed shells, seam side down, over sauce in one layer.
Spoon remaining sauce evenly over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until shells are heated through.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beer beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain grease when beef is browned.
Add Ro-tel tomatoes, beans, garlic, salt, mushrooms and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add beer if you want to.
If not, add 1 cup water and simmer for 45 minutes. May add more water if you want it soupier.
You can't really taste the beer when added.
Try it, you'll like it.

title: applesauce-strawberry bread
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine raisins and brandy.
Add enough water to cover raisins.
Bring to a simmer.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Drain.

title: andy's lazy man's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add seasonings.
Add paste, sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes (mixture will be thin). In a 13 x 9-inch pan, ladle in about 1 1/2 cups mixture.
Next put egg noodles on (uncooked), ladle in more mixture on top, then noodles again; repeat until there are 3 layers.
Put cheese on second and top layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Be sure to cover tightly with foil.

title: spoonburgers(club member: john waters)
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet over medium heat. Add other ingredients. Cover and cook slowly until meat is done.
Serve on hot buns or with rice or other foods.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put uncooked chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: In 4-quart cast-iron pot, pour in peas and bacon drippings or the salt pork.
Add hot water to cover peas.
Cook slow 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.
Salt to taste.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: elegantly scalloped potatoes
directions: Oil a 3-quart casserole ('r 2 different smaller dishes; freeze one fur later).
Dump ingredients in bowl 'ceptin 'maters, rice, 'n several tablespoons oil, vinegah 'n watah, 'n mix.
Now layer maters.
Kiver wid 1/2 uv vegetubles.
Sprinkle 1/2 uv rice, a few more maters 'n vegetables n rice 'n top wid maters.
Pore 3 tablespoons olive oil, vinegah 'n watah over top 'n bake kivered fur 2 hours in 350° stove.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 13 x 9 baking pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Pour into hot jars.
Process 45 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: micro brownies
directions: Melt butter in microwave-safe bowl.
Add vanilla, eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat well with a whisk.
Add flour, cocoa and nuts. Pour into a well-greased and floured microwave-safe pie plate. Bake Full power for five minutes.
Let stand for ten minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, butter, milk, eggs and vanilla and beat with mixer until creamy.
Place in deep casserole.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl and set aside. Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly. Slowly add flour mixture in three parts, mixing well after each addition.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick and cut with cookie cutters. Paint with egg wash and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 40 (2-inch) cookies.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and water.
Cool.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix and sift twice the flour, salt, sugar and baking soda.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fix dough to box recipe.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Cook sausage and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts. Let sausage mixture cool.
Make 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread sausage mixture evenly over dough.
Roll up and tuck ends under.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk and eggs; mix well. Pour into 2 waxed paper lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chopped nuts and cinnamon may be sprinkled over crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients into a 1-quart casserole dish and cover. Microwave at High until apples are tender (7 to 10 minutes). Mash apples to desired consistency.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water, sugar, and cloves for 15 minutes.
Add orange, pineapple, and lemon juices.
Remove cloves from tea.
Makes 2 gallons and will keep 2-3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: no-bake yum-yum bars
directions: Line an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with whole graham crackers.
In saucepan, heat brown sugar, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil quickly; remove from heat and add 1 cup crushed graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Pour hot mixture over whole wafers in dish.
Put whole graham crackers on top of mixture and press until mixture eases through a little.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Yields 12 bars.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix and bake as you would any other cake (about 45 minutes at 350°).

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix with 1 can of crushed pineapple.
Butter a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan; pour batter on pan and bake as directed on cake mix box.
Cool.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in waffle iron. Add scoop of ice cream to each serving.
Batter will keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook wild rice by directions.
Spread rice in a dish.
Mix broccoli, onion, cheese, mushroom soup and milk together.
Spread over rice.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Flour and saute for 10 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and place in baking dish.
Cut onions and mushrooms and add to same pan.
Saute until tender and layer over chicken.
In same pan add broth, butter and wine.
Bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy meat loaves
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Combine with eggs and milk and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir into meat mixture and shape into six individual loaves.
Roll each in bread crumbs and place in a lightly-greased 9 X 13 pan.
Spread with chili sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and oatmeal.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet orange chicken(allergy free)
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Drain.
Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: fettuccine al fresco
directions: Heat oil in saucepan. Add ham, onion and garlic and cook until onion is tender. Add pasta sauce and parsley. Heat through. Serve over fettuccine with cheese.

title: unbelievable sweet potato and pecan casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 8 x 13 pan.

title: microwave tuna stroganoff
directions: Combine tuna, soup and mushrooms in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat on full power, 6 to 8 minutes, or until bubbling. Stir twice during heating.
Stir in sour cream.
Garnish with parsley if desired and serve over noodles.

title: awesome cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla; beat until light.
Stir in milk.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Chill 1 hour or longer.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into shapes and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips and mix with peanut butter.
Add this to 6 cups of Rice Krispies and mix well.
Pour mixture onto a cookie sheet and spread.
Let cool and set up.
Let 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream set out until softened.
Pull chocolate mixture apart in pieces and mix with softened ice cream.
Mix well and refreeze.

title: sis lawson's famous spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef with half of the salt and pepper.
Drain off fat. In 6 quart pan, put beef and stir in rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside.	Mix milk and pudding and add Cool Whip.
Add pudding mixture to creamed mixture.
Layer crushed cookies with creamed mixture making several layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put croutons in bottom of pan with cheese next.
Mix rest of ingredients, except bacon or sausage. Pour over top.
Put foil over top and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, put bacon or sausage over top. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meatless jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in water, tomatoes, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, red pepper and fennel seed. Bring to a boil. Add rice. Reduce heat to low;

cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans. Cover and simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Makes 5 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix onion, mayonnaise and vegetables and place in casserole dish.
Cover mixture with cheese then crushed crackers.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: rice and chicken jambalaya
directions: Cook onion, celery, carrots, rice and seasonings in chicken broth for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add chicken and parsley; cook 15 minutes more.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raisin pancakes
directions: Combine the baking mix, shredded cereal and sugar in a large bowl.
Beat together milk and eggs in medium-size bowl.
Pour milk mixture into the dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moist; do not overmix.
Stir in raisins.

title: ranger stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix together soup, beans, tomatoes, celery and onions.
Add seasonings, add salt and pepper to taste. Heat for 30 minutes and serve.
I add extra potatoes and carrots.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bring the chicken broth to a boil.
Stir in flour and butter and mix to a smooth paste.
Stir constantly until the broth is thick and smooth.
Lower heat, stir in milk, chicken and vegetables and heat through.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: bread cookies(easy for children to make.)
directions: Remove crusts from one side of bread on each slice.
Roll each slice with rolling pin as flat as possible.
Butter the bread on one side, then spread with preserves.
Roll bread up, jelly roll fashion, beginning with crustless side.
Drizzle rolls with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° for 25 minutes more.
Remove rolls from the oven and immediately roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour.
Cut each roll into 3 pieces and coat with 10x sugar.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add milk, buttermilk, eggs and oil. Stir until well blended. Add onion and mix well. Batter should be stiff. Drop rounded tablespoons into hot deep-fat fryer. Turn when hush puppy floats and brown both sides to golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Makes about 24.

title: hawaiian ham filling
directions: Mix well and spread on sandwich bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curried mayonnaise dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and slowly add to mayonnaise.
Good for carrots, celery, cauliflower and radishes.

title: fudge nut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to margarine mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool and garnish with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into churn.
Finish filling the churn with milk.

title: virginia box bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add eggs, salt, sugar, butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Add enough flour to
make a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 6 to 8 minutes.
Put in a greased bowl. Turn once so top is greased.
Let rise until doubled.
On a lightly floured board, roll out dough to fit a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place dough in pan.
Using a sharp knife, cut dough into 12 squares.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican chex mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan until melted.
Remove and stir in seasoning.
Add Chex mix until all pieces are coated.
Mix in nuts.
Heat 20 minutes, stirring midway.
Remove and sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Toss to coat all pieces.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Let stand in cold water overnight.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars.
To each quart, add amounts shown of alum, garlic, dill and red pepper.
Combine salt, water and vinegar; heat to boiling.
Fill jars.
Put grape leaf in each jar.
Seal. Makes 6 to 8 quarts.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip. Spoon some pudding into bottom of pan to start, ending with pudding on top.
Garnish as desired.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan; add onions.
Fry until soft and yellow.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add water, stock and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer slowly 45 minutes.
Good served in bowls topped with circles of toast sprinkled with cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet chunk pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers.
Put cucumbers in a stone jar or stainless steel container.
Add salt and 1/4 cup vinegar to 2 quarts water; bring to boiling.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover with diner plate or glass pie plate.
Fill jar with water and use to hold plate under brine.
Cover and let stand 2 weeks in a cool place.
(If scum forms, remove it each day.)
Drain, discarding brine and cut cucumbers into 1 inch chunks.
Add alum to cucumbers and cover with cold water; let stand 24 hours.
Rinse well and drain.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag; add to remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain, reserving syrup.
Heat syrup to boiling and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Repeat the last step three times.
Pack pickles into hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Remove spice bag.
Bring syrup to boiling.
Pour boiling hot over pickles, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust caps. Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield: about 3 pints.

title: very easy beef casserole
directions: Combine, bake covered 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over thin egg noodles or rice with salad and rolls.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix and garnish with parsley flakes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Place all ingredients in sauce pan and bring to a boil.
Take 2 heaping Tbsp. corn starch, mix with a little water and stir into cherry mixture to thicken filling.
Place in pie crust and make lattice strips to go on top of pie.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar and continue beating.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Drop by small spoonfuls, far apart, onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes only.

title: mint brownie cups
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and mint extract.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Line a muffin pan with 12 cupcake liners.
Fill each with 2 tablespoons batter.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes until a toothpick barely comes out clean.
Remove to cool on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.
The cups will sink slightly in the middle.
Garnish with sliced strawberries, if available.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and let simmer slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes, stirring after one minute.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes about 2 dozen pieces.
May be doubled.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and mix with cooked and drained spinach.
Pour into greased casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: turkey divine
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Arrange broccoli in a shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Top with slices of turkey.
Blend soup and milk and pour over all. Mix cheese with potato chips and sprinkle over soup.
Bake at 350° until top is lightly browned and sauce is bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add syrup, vanilla, powdered milk and sugar.
Knead until well mixed.
Roll into roll, then cut when needed.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Unroll each crescent roll individually.
Combine remainder of ingredients and spoon out equally on each roll.
Roll crescent roll up and place seam side down on greased cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: deviled short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs on all sides.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients except onion and pour over browned ribs.
Place sliced onion on top and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Skim off fat before serving.
If desired, thicken with flour.

title: eggnog
directions: Place all ingredients, except nutmeg, in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into serving glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: no fat cheesecake
directions: Make sure cream cheese is at room temperature before mixing. Add sugar to cream cheese and blend.
Add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix yeast in warm water, mix dry ingredients and make hole in center.
Add yeast mixture.
Form into pretzels.
Place on cookie sheet, brush top with beaten eggs.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry tea punch
directions: Prepare tea by combining bags with 2 cups boiling water. Allow to steep 10 minutes; remove tea bags.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Dip pecan halves into mixture and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook for 30 minutes at 250°.
Turn oven off and leave in 30 minutes longer.

title: spanakopita:  greek spinach salad
directions: Clean, stem and chop spinach; salt lightly and cook, adding no water for 5 minutes.
Cook the onion in butter and salt lightly. When soft, combine with the cheese, eggs, flour, basil and cottage cheese.
Spread melted butter on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place strudel leaf (filo) in pan and brush with butter.
Keep layering dough, one on top of another, each with butter.
When you have a pile of 8, spread on half of the filling.
Continue with another stack of 8.
Apply remaining filling.
Pile as many more layers of filo and butter as your pan will allow.
Fold excess dough down along the edges.
Butter the top leaf and sprinkle with anise or fennel seed.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen servings.
Takes 1 1/2 hours preparation time.

title: bulldog brittle
directions: Melt butter and sugar over low heat.
Pour over crackers, then sprinkle with pecans.
Let harden.
Enjoy!

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: Drain beans and corn.
If salsa is very juicy you may want to drain a little liquid off of it.
Mix these ingredients in a bowl.
Chop cilantro and add.
Add a dash of lime juice for added tartness. Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.

title: layered nacho dip no. 2(yields 24 servings)
directions: Combine beans and sasoningg mix; spread bean mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with corn chips. Yields about 8 cups.

title: light and fluffy cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in pie crust and chill for 4 hours until set. Cover with cherry pie filling.

title: old-time popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in slow oven.
Butter sides of saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients except vanilla.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Add vanilla.
Pour slowly over hot popped corn, stirring just to mix thoroughly.
Butter hands lightly; shape into balls.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: pumpkin bread(makes three 9-inch loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Spoon batter into 3 (9-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until well done.
Let bread cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
After completely cooled, can be frozen.
Wrap in plastic first, then wrap in aluminum foil.

title: art's michigan sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients with tomato sauce and raw hamburg in skillet.
Simmer on medium heat until hamburg is cooked (1/2 to 1 hour).
Hamburg will become very fine.
Add Frank's hot sauce to desired level of "hotness."

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes. Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
Spread 1/2 noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the meat; repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Place 1-quart casserole dish in a baking pan on oven rack.
Pour mix into dish.
Pour boiling water into pan around dish about 1-inch. Slide rack carefully into oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: lentil roast(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly.
Pile in baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Add and mix with potatoes.
Can be stored in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Also good on cucumbers.

title: christmas eve barbecue
directions: Cut onion and pepper into small pieces.
Combine with ground beef in skillet.
Brown hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Put back in skillet and add jar of chili sauce and a little ketchup.
Mix together and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.
If it gets dry, add more ketchup.

title: crock-pot meatballs
directions: Prepare sauce first and put in crock-pot to simmer while preparing meatballs.
Turn crock-pot to high while preparing sauce.
Put all ingredients in pot; stir together well.
Leave simmering until meatballs are ready.

title: carrot kugel
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
To be served hot as a vegetable.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and dice potatoes.
Fry bacon to crisp.
Reserve fat to make dressing.
Add bacon to potato.
Mix remaining ingredients in bacon fat; cook until thick and glossy.
Pour over potatoes.
Makes six 1/2-cup servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash the cucumbers thoroughly; drain.
Cut unpeeled cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
In a large bowl, combine the cucumber slices, onions, garlic and salt; cover with the crushed ice or ice cubes.
Mix thoroughly and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain off the liquid and remove the garlic.
Combine the sugar, spices and vinegar and heat just to a boil.
Add the cucumber and onion slices; simmer together for 10 minutes.
Pack loosely in clean, hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch of headroom; remove air bubbles. Adjust lids; process in boiling water bath (212°F/100°C) for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Complete seals, if necessary.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in oil; remove.
Brown ground chuck, stirring often.
Add soups, mushrooms and salt.
Cook rice in boiling salt water.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in ham and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix all together and put in casserole. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, egg and 1 teaspoon vegetable oil.
Insert wooden skewer in each hot dog.
Dip in batter, coating completely.
Deep fry at 325° until golden, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix that has been mixed with 1 cup butter. Bake 30 minutes.

title: no bake peanut brownies
directions: Combine crumbs, peanuts, sugar and peanut butter using a whisk or pastry blender.
In a small saucepan, melt the chocolate chips and milk over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Pour remaining chocolate mixture over crumb mixture and stir until well blended. Spread evenly in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Frost with reserved chocolate mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: *pineapple nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in milk, lemon juice, pineapple with syrup and finally, the chopped nuts.
Mix all dry ingredients and add.
Stir just until all ingredients are dampened and evenly blended.
Put into a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Line bottom of pan with greased paper.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: shrimp dinner
directions: Combine contents of rice and seasoning packets, water and 2 tablespoons butter in medium saucepan.
Bring to a vigorous boil. Stir in asparagus.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until all water is absorbed about 5 minutes.
While rice simmers, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, garlic and salt.
Stir-fry until shrimp are opaque, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir lemon peel into cooked rice and sprinkle with carrot, if desired.
Serve shrimp alongside rice.
Serves 4.

title: scripture cake
directions: First to make this cake you must read your Bible.
Each ingredient is
mentioned
in a verse from the Bible.
Feed the soul as
well
as
the body.
Follow King Soloman's advice for making a
good
boy
and
you
will have a good cake, Proverbs 23:14.
Bake
in
a
slow
oven, Leviticus 2:4 (325°).
If you prefer a frosting, caramel will enrich the flavor.

title: joy's shrimp salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain.
Stir in French dressing while warm and chill in refrigerator.
Add in rest of ingredients and chill.	May garnish with dill weed. Serves 6.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup, maple syrup and melted butter or margarine.
Add chopped walnuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely before cutting.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Prepare chicken gravy as directed. Add all ingredients except cheese.
Remove the stems from and clean mushrooms.
Fill with meat mixture and top with cheese and bake at 400 for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: In a large saucepan, mix eggs, milk and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture coats metal spoon.
Remove from heat.
Cool quickly.
Place pan in sink or bowl of ice water and stir for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in rum, bourbon and vanilla. Chill 4 to 24 hours.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually adding sugar.
Mix together baking powder, cracker crumbs, pecans and vanilla.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6-8.

title: country franks stir-fry
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook frankfurter slices until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove frankfurter slices to bowl.
In same skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook green peppers, onions, oregano, salt and pepper until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Add frankfurters; toss gently.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix cheese and onions (keep out a little cheese to top enchilada with).
Next, heat the enchilada sauce.
Dip the tortillas in sauce to soften.
Fill with cheese-onions and roll up.
Place them, seam side down, in a glass baking pan.
Pour the rest of the enchilada sauce over and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is bubbly.

title: basic oven fried fish
directions: Combine salt and milk.
Dip fish in milk, then roll in dry crumbs.
Place portions in a well-greased baking dish and drizzle with melted butter.
Place baking dish on top shelf of preheated 500° oven and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until portions flake easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garlic scalloped potatoes
directions: In casserole dish, rub sides and bottom with butter.
Layer potatoes, salt, pepper, garlic and butter dots until dish is almost full.
Pour heavy cream over potatoes until almost covered. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Turn heat up last 10 minutes to 400° to brown top.
Serves 6.

title: hobo stew
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and save drippings.
Brown hamburger in bacon drippings.
Combine water, gravy mix, salt, pepper and chili powder into meat.
Add cubed potatoes; cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
