Add green peppers, corn and kidney beans; cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Add and remove ingredients to accomodate your taste.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour uncooked rice into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
Mix soups and water together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: peggy's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; cool and separate meat from the bone.
Separate also the broth from the chicken.
Cut up the chicken into bite sized pieces.
In a large bowl, add in the plain flour, ice water slowly and salt.
Add to this the Crisco, until well blended into a pie crust dough.
Roll out the dough with a rolling pin and cut into strips about 1/2-inch wide and pan length long.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In a large dish, add boiling water to jello.
Add buttermilk, crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt until smooth. Add pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Stir in whipped cream and cranberry.
Pour into loaf pan and freeze.

title: texas ladies champion chili
directions: Brown meat with seasoned salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; cook 30 minutes.
Add paprika, onion powder, cayenne, jalapeno powder, beef base, beef broth, chicken base, chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until meat is tender, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until meat is done.

title: beef mushroom buns
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add soup, mushrooms, onions and Worcestershire sauce to beef.
Cut bread dough into 8 pieces. Form into balls (flour board and hands), then pat into 5-inch diameter circles.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons beef mixture in center, then pull all dough edges to center and pinch together tightly.
Place buns, smooth side up, on greased baking sheet. Make steam vents with knife or scissors.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°, or until well browned.

title: crawfish stew
directions: Put oil in heavy pan. Add flour and slowly brown well for roux. Add onion, bell peppers, celery and garlic. Cook until transparent. Add crawfish tails and cook about 30 minutes. Serve over rice. Sprinkle green onions on top.

title: oven baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Dip chicken in egg, then into the bread crumbs.
Coat well.
Arrange chicken in a 9 X 13 glass baking dish and bake for 20 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a platter.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; spread over beans.
Sprinkle lettuce, onion, jalapeno chips and cheese over mixture.
Cut tomatoes in half and garnish. Let chill 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with chips and salsa.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and onion powder together.
Fold in cheese and dried beef.
Add green pepper, if desired.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: best potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
(Most of the liquid will be absorbed.)
Add milk and butter; heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: seafood open face sandwich
directions: Combine softened Velveeta cheese and butter.
Stir flaked crabmeat into cheese and butter mixture and set aside.
Toast white bread on one side (in broiler or oven).
Heap cheese and crabmeat mixture on untoasted side of bread.
Place under broiler until bubbly.
Watch carefully!

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into 3-inch logs.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill for several hours.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with apples, brushed with lemon juice to prevent browning.

title: low calorie mississippi mud
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until slightly brown. Cool.

title: butterscotch popcorn crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a heavy gauge saucepan, combine butterscotch morsels, corn syrup and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils.
Place popcorn and nuts in a large greased roasting pan.
Pour butterscotch mixture over popcorn; toss to coat well.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from oven; stir every 10 minutes until slightly cooled.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: sweet-sour country ribs
directions: Put ribs in a single layer in large, shallow casserole.
Pour soy sauce over meat and sprinkle with garlic.
Pour juices from canned pineapple into pan with ribs.
Reserve pineapple chunks. Sprinkle with coriander.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until ribs are very tender, basting occasionally.
Remove ribs onto platter.

title: low-fat tuna casserole (hot)
directions: Boil macaroni in 1-quart saucepan and steam broccoli.
Drain and mix with tuna in bowl.
Grate cheese and spread pinch of garlic over mix.
Stir and place in casserole dish with cover.
Place in oven preheated at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out and put on cooking rack.
Garnish with parsley and serve.
Will feed 6 to 8 adults.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: kraut
directions: Slice or chop cabbage.
Press down into clean jars.
Add per quart:
2 teaspoons salt, 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon sugar. Fill with cold water and seal with lids.
Place in dark cool room.
A little of the water will seep out.
Takes about 2 weeks to pickle.

title: peachy cake
directions: Place peaches with juice in a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle on nuts, then coconut.
Melt margarine and pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (20-25 minutes).

title: frosted delights
directions: Place raisins and water in small saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Cool slightly and add soda to pan; mix.
Set aside.

title: chicken divine
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Parboil broccoli.
Place broccoli in bottom of an oblong baking dish.
Place chicken
on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over sauce.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake entire entree at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the best egg pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add milk, vanilla and melted butter last.
Mix by hand; do not use electric mixer.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
A really simple egg pie that comes out fine every time.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Sprinkle crushed cookies into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 cup oleo over crumbs and freeze.
Combine remaining ingredients except for ice cream and boil for 4 minutes.
Cool and pour over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and freeze. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until cheese melts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday berry bubbly
directions: Fill champagne flutes 1/3 full with cranberry-raspberry drink. Fill to the top with your favorite champagne for a beautiful holiday drink.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil whole chicken until tender (approximately 1 hour).
Let cool.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Reserve broth.
Discard skin and bones.
Break spaghetti into 1 1/2-inch pieces and boil until tender (approximately 10 minutes).
Saute mushrooms in melted butter.
Add chicken soup and sour cream until creamy.
Combine soup mixture, chicken and spaghetti; stir in Beau Monde.
Spoon mixture into buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add 1 cup broth on top to keep from drying out.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bacon poles(microwave recipe)
directions: Wrap each bread stick with a slice of bacon "Barber Pole Fashion".
Place about 10 sticks in microwave pan lined with paper towel and cover with paper towel.
Cook on High for 5 to 7 minutes, turning once during cooking.
Place on clean paper towel to cool and get crisp.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Cream Crisco,
sugar
and oleomargarine.
Add egg yolks one at a time
to this mixture.
Mix together soda and buttermilk and let stand
for	a
few	minutes.
Add
alternately to creamed mixture flour and buttermilk.
Add pecans and coconut. Fold in egg whites. Beat
egg whites stiff before folding in. Bake in	3
round greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Using yellow cake mix, follow directions on box.
Add coconut flavoring to mix.
Bake in 9 inch x 13 inch pan at 350 degrees.

title: layered lemon pie
directions: Crumble chocolate wafers in blender.
Mix with 1/4 cup butter and pat into pie pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, sugar and salt. Stir to dissolve.
Pour half of lemon mixture into eggs.
Return eggs to rest of lemon mixture and cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Place half of ice cream in cookie crust.
Freeze. Place half of lemon mixture in crust.
Freeze.
Repeat layers. Freeze.
Garnish with cookie crumbs or chocolate curls.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, bring squash to a boil in an inch of water.
Add onion and cook, covered, over moderately high heat for 10 minutes, until squash is tender. Drain; coarsely mash squash and onion.
Add 1/2 tablespoon of margarine, egg white, half of the cracker crumbs, nutmeg and pepper and stir until blended.
Coat an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Spoon squash mixture into pan; smooth with spatula.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Add enough water to cover all ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on high 30 minutes, and then on low 6 hours.
Serve while hot.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach custard dessert
directions: Grease a square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix, milk, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Spread in the pan; arrange peach slices on top.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle over peach slices.
Mix sour cream and egg; drizzle over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm and, if desired, with whipped cream.

title: soup from the pantry
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, mix all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook linguini according to directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cool water.
Combine all ingredients, except 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place remaining Mozzarella cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: sandy tarts
directions: Soften butter; add ingredients in order named.
Mix thoroughly.
With hands, form into crescent shapes.
Bake slowly in a 300° oven until golden brown.
While still warm, sift powdered sugar over them generously.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Slice layers to make 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream, flavoring and 1 1/2 packages coconut.
Place between layers only.
Mix 1/2 package coconut with Cool Whip and cover sides and top with mixture.
Let stand at least 24 hours.
Will keep at least a week in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat together the first five ingredients.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Chill.
Then roll in ball and sprinkle with nuts.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Grind Oreo cookies.
Layer; start with cookies, pudding, then cream cheese mixture and so on.

title: cracked wheat bread
directions: Soak wheat in water overnight.
Combine milk, salt, shortening and molasses in a mixing bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Add soaked wheat and dissolved yeast to milk mixture.
Add 3 cups flour and beat 2 minutes until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Combine cheese and place in large glass baking pan.
Spread jalapenos on top; set aside.
Mix flour, milk and eggs well.
Pour mixture over top of cheese and peppers.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Let thicken and then add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with thin slices of honeydew melon.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil carrots for 15 minutes in salt water until tender. Drain.
Bring Mazola oil, vinegar, sugar and tomato soup to a boil.
Arrange alternate layers of carrots, onion and bell pepper. Pour tomato mixture over.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 to 2 days.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water together; set aside to cool.
Cream together oleo, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, salt and cinnamon; add oatmeal mixture and blend well. Add flour and soda. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy shrimp etouffee
directions: Season shrimp with salt, pepper, cayenne and garlic.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in heavy pot.
Add vegetables and garlic (if using fresh) and cook slowly, uncovered, until onions wilt. Add shrimp.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water. Add this to shrimp and then add soup.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with rice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Set aside. Combine cornmeal mix, flour, onion and bacon.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add egg, buttermilk and 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour oil into Dutch oven. Heat to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoon into oil.
Fry a few at a time, turning once, to golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve immediately.
Yield: 20 hush puppies.

title: pineapple mandarin salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set for several hours or overnight.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt, soda and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Divide into 3 layers.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer chicken, then broccoli in casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° covered 20 minutes, uncovered 10 minutes for a total of 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind squash and onion together.
In a bowl mix with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Chop pepper.
Add to vegetables.
In pan, combine all ingredients except vegetables. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Heat to a full boil.
Pour in jars and process for 10 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oatmeal.
Drop onto waxed paper with teaspoon. Makes 5 dozen.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash, covered, in boiling water 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Mash enough squash to measure 1 cup. Combine squash and egg.
Stir well.
Combine flour and cornmeal; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion.
Stir until blended. Drop squash mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: soup for dieters
directions: Cut vegetables.
Put in large pot.
Add water and soup mix to cover vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer until very tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add egg yolks and milk; cook until thickened. Pour in pie shell.
Beat egg whites. Add a pinch of salt and cream of tartar; beat until slightly stiff.
Add 2 level tablespoons of sugar per egg white.
Beat until stiff.
Cover pie with meringue and cook until brown.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix yellow cake mix and oats.
Add butter.
Mix.

title: potatoes hashed in cream
directions: Peel the day of use, cube, cover with 1 pt. heavy cream, salt and butter.
Cook 1 hour.
Transfer to casserole, dot with butter and grated cheese and paprika.
Bake another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peppermint meringue(good holiday cookie)
directions: Place one oven rack in middle of oven and second rack directly above it.
Heat oven to 225°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil. Beat egg whites in a large bowl with electric mixer until foamy. Add salt and cream of tartar, beat until soft peaks form when beaters are lifted.

Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Continue beating 5 to 6 minutes until stiff, smooth and glossy. Spoon into large Ziploc with bottom corner (1 inch) snipped off. Holding bag upright, squeeze mounds 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches high onto cookie sheet.
Lightly sprinkle candy over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Turn off oven.
Leave door ajar and let meringues cool in oven until crisp and dry.
Store loosely covered in cool dry place.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, biscuit mix, egg, oil, and milk together.
Spread half the mix in a greased 8 x 8 x 2 in. pan.
Layer green chilies and sliced Jack cheese over corn mixture.
Spread remaining corn mixture over top.
Bake at 400 for 30 minutes until browned. Serves 6.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In medium bowl, mix refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch platter.
Blend ripe avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup salsa until smooth.
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Top with lettuce, cheese, remaining salsa*
and olive slices.
Serve with tortilla chips.
May be refrigerated up to 24 hours.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream 1 stick margarine and sugar together; set aside.
Melt 1 stick margarine and candy bars in double boiler; set aside.
Add beaten eggs to creamed sugar and oleo mixture.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add to candy mixture.
Combine both mixtures together.
Add vanilla and flour, a small amount at a time.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in layers or stem pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: rodeo beans
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock pot.
Cook on medium heat for 4 - 6 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert or service bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm.

title: oatmeal-molasses cookies(low calorie)
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until blended.
Add molasses, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients in a bowl, stirring mixture well. Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well to combine.
Drop dough by level tablespoons onto cookie sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks.
Yield:
32 cookies.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt oleo and add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Use drippings as sauce.
Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook salt pork, then add beef floured to brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Place broccoli and rice in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in half of cheese spread.
Melt butter in skillet, add onion and celery and cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in soup and milk, then season to taste (salt and pepper).
Pour sauce over rice and broccoli mixture; mix well.
Top casserole with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: eleanor's egg and noodle pie
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Add eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste and stir to cover noodles.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Add noodles.

title: skinny "french fries"
directions: Pierce squash several places and bake whole 1 1/2 hours at 350° or
steam
for
1 hour.
If baked, turn halfway during baking time.
Cut in half; remove seeds.
Scrape out meat with fork, producing a spaghetti-like texture.
Serve with favorite spaghetti sauce and ground meat, if desired.

title: layered spaghetti casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook beef in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until brown; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Remove from heat.
Mix spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Spread in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients and add to potato salad or macaroni salad.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Cover; refrigerate 4 to 8 hours. Garnish with tomatoes.

title: roquefort grapes
directions: To Toast Nuts:
Preheat oven to 275°.
Spread nuts on baking sheet and bake until toasted.
Almonds should be a light golden color.
Pecans and walnuts should smell toasted, but not burned.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin spice and salt.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: easy cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 14-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Mix yeast mixture with buttermilk, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda. Cut in shortening.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Do not knead.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pinch off amount as needed. Knead, roll and cut to bake.
Do not allow to rise.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Can be refrigerated up to 5 days.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Combine cheese and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix lemon pudding with milk until smooth and thick, spread over Cool Whip layer.
Spread leftover Cool Whip over the lemon layer, sprinkle with extra nuts.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak lima beans overnight.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, tomatoes and bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Great dish to take to a potluck!!

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on cake box.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter or margarine and evaporated milk in double boiler.
Pour caramel mixture over hot cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and chips.
Pour rest of batter over top and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: tortillas chicken wraps
directions: Combine chicken, picante sauce, chili powder and garlic powder in a large skillet; mix well. Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add 3/4 cup cheese and beans to chicken mixture; mix well. Wrap tortillas in a kitchen towel and microwave on High for 1 minute.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper.
Drain when all is done.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, mushroom soup and tomato juice. Simmer for 1 hour on low heat and serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: macaroon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Place egg whites in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form; set aside.
Combine egg yolks, shortening and butter in separate mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in extracts, alternately beat in flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add coconut; blend well. Gently fold in egg whites with rubber spatula until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool completely. Decorate with toasted coconut and confectioners sugar before serving, if desired.

title: mexicali cornbread pie
directions: Crush cornbread stuffing mix while still in bag.
Pour into bowl and add water, melted butter and beaten egg.
Mix together and press into 9-inch pie pan.
Saute onion, garlic, pepper and beef in oil; discard fat.
Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon, cumin, salsa and beans.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Spoon onto cornbread crust. Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Let stand 5 minutes or until cheese has melted before serving.
Makes
6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender in salt water.
Saute onions in part of the oleo; do not brown.
Drain squash.
Mix other ingredients. Grease baking dish with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Add the mixture and the squash.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken la gumbo
directions: Fry bacon, then saute onions and garlic in bacon grease.
Add flour and file and brown.
Add to chicken broth then add bacon, sausage and chicken.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes then cook another 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: japanese chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and salt.
Marinate chicken in mixed ingredients for 2 or 3 hours.
Cook at 325°, covered, until tender.
Uncover and cook down.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, butter and pecans in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil over low heat.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place graham crackers in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan; spoon butter mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool and chill slightly.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork and add to jello with the nuts.
Fold in cream cheese.
Pour all into 8 x 8 x 2 pan.

title: new sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cream cheese and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture into pie crusts.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (melt oleo).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thoroughly set.
Use 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and put back in oven to melt (optional).

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat roll dough out on jelly roll tin; bake according to instructions and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and spices and spread on cooled dough.
Chop vegetables very fine and spread over cheese topping.
Pat down; top with grated cheese.
Pat down. Cut into squares and serve.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Saute onion with butter; add milk, taco sauce and chilies. Cut cheese in small pieces and add to liquid.
Heat on low to melt cheese.

title: nut bread
directions: Put
together
in
order given.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into greased bread tin.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together last five ingredients in pan.
Pour over chicken and put stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Any vegetable may be used.

title: beth's brownies
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour and chocolate syrup; mix well. Spoon into greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes or until brownies test done.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top of baked brownies.

title: artichoke-spinach casserole
directions: Place artichokes in a casserole.
Place spinach on top of the artichokes.
Beat the cream cheese and butter until smooth; add milk.
Spread over top of the spinach.
Top with a grind of fresh black pepper and the Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered the first 30 minutes and uncovered the last 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: north carolina cookies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in currants.
This dough is very soft.
It's a good idea to chill it.
Divide into sections and roll thin.
Cut.
Grease electric frypan lightly.
Set at 250° and bake 5 minutes on each side.
Be careful because they burn easily.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in blender.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
While still hot, add all of the first mixture together with the macaroni.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Feeds a crowd.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Put papers into cupcake tins (12).
Put 1 vanilla wafer on bottom of papers.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Put cherries on top.
Freezes well (without cherries).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole.
Layer accordingly.
Peel and slice carrots and place in bottom of casserole.
Trim pork chops and place on carrots.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chop green onions (tops too).
Place on chops.
Spread cream-style corn over all. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 275°.
Last 15 minutes uncover, turn oven to 375° to brown top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening together until light, scraping sides of bowl often. Add eggs, one at a time, then milk.
Beat until smooth and fluffy. Add flour mixture and mashed bananas alternately to cream mixture, beating until smooth.
Gently fold in chopped nuts. Turn batter into lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: brunch dish
directions: Mix all the ingredients, saving black olives and 1/2 of the crumbled bacon.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top
with black olives and bacon.
You may want to spray the pan with Pam if you use a metal pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make small balls and make a little hole with a thimble.
Fill with apricot jelly or any favorite jelly.
Bake at 375°.
The round end of a clothespin may be used to make the hole.

title: red magic meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, 1/3 cup ketchup, onion, egg, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Form mixture into 8 x 4 x 1 1/2 inch loaf and place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: lemon souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar.
Grate rind of lemon into sugar and egg yolk mixture.
Add salt to flour and stir into egg yolk mixture alternately with the milk.

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Put pepperoncini and the liquid from the jar around the roast.
Cook on low for 12 hours.
Remove pepperoncini.
Shred meat.
Serve on buns or sourdough bread.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Brown and drain the turkey with the onion.
Add the spices, the tomatoes and paste.
Simmer.

title: fudgemallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder in large bowl.
Blend peanut butter, vegetable oil and egg.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in flour, then vanilla and peanuts.
Shape into ball.
Place in ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for ten minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Unwrap crescent rolls. Separate into 2 rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips. Place strips on top to form lattice.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes until onions are golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make cheese sauce by melting margarine in saucepan.
Add flour or cornstarch to make smooth paste.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and add liquid from drained asparagus and also Pet milk, stirring until smooth.
Place back on medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and Ragu.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic salt to noodles and layer noodles and meat sauce, ending with meat sauce.
Combine cream cheese and milk and warm in saucepan; stir until smooth. Pour this over noodles and meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ma's greek cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate with orange juice and flour (flour has been sifted with baking soda and baking powder) a little at a time.
This should be a soft dough.
Shape as desired (braid, cross, etc.)
Brush with egg and milk mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to each cup of water or to your own taste.

title: shiny top cobbler
directions: Spread fruit in well-greased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.
In medium bowl, stir flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, the milk, butter, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt until well blended (batter will be thick).
Spoon over fruit. Spread to edges of baking dish; set aside.

title: denise's "d" pie
directions: Mix together in order given; pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed pita toasts with feta cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pita rounds on a baking sheet and brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper. Bake until crispy and lightly golden, about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and break pitas in half.
Slice Feta cheese, drizzle with olive oil and serve with pitas.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients well; beat whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Fry by dropping tablespoonfuls into grease.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix butter, pretzels and 3 teaspoons sugar together and form a crust in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Next, combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip in mixer and pour over crust.
Mix Jell-O mix and boiling water and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and add cocoa; cool slightly.
Beat egg and add sugar.
Add margarine and cocoa mix.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in an oven preheated to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour. Add rhubarb and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until custard is set.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt oleo.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.

Add hot water; stir again. Blend in sugar, flour, vanilla and milk with a wire whisk until batter is smooth. Mix in pecans and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until custard sets. Serve cool with whipped topping.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, Wesson oil, milk, sour cream and vanilla.
Then fold in the chocolate chips and bar of sweet chocolate.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan (large).
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Test may be done sooner.

title: mexican enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet, drain off excess fat. Add onions and seasonings.
Add tomato sauce, enchilada sauce and green chilies.
Cook slowly until meat is done.
Grease large baking dish (9 x 13-inches).

title: squash and tomato casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain in colander.
Beat eggs together with chopped onion.
Add squash and butter.
Cover bottom of casserole with squash mixture. Slice fresh tomatoes thinly
and place on top of squash.	Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: moette punch (non-alcoholic drink)(8 servings)
directions: Add soda to fruit juices; sweeten to taste.
Pour into punch bowl; add scoops of sherbet.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with mixture of crackers and oleo.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Good with ham.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze several hours in pan.
Slice and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: little smokies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Add barbecue sauce and little smokies.
Put in crock-pot or slow cooker for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Measure flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Sift twice onto wax paper and return to sifter.
Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugar gradually, creaming after each addition until mixture is well blended.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture; blend well.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple. Fold Cool Whip and cottage cheese into fruit. Sprinkle dry Jell-O on top and fold in. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.
Serves 10.

title: unusual dip
directions: Chop peppers and onions finely.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and Serve with chips.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish, mix soup, water, rice, paprika and pepper.
Place chicken on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.
Prep time: 5 minutes.
Cooking Time: 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until done; drain.
Add Italian dressing and mix until pasta is well coated.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing after each addition.
Refrigerate before eating.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into eighths.
Arrange in unbaked shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with the flour; cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Add water, salt and cook.
Cook white sauce of flour, milk, pepper, margarine and some cheese.
Drain cooked cabbage.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add crushed crackers and sauce and mix.
Top with your favorite cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
My recipe.

title: danish pastry
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Beat eggs; melt 1/3 cup margarine and add to yeast, along with sugar and salt.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been rubbed with shortening.
Chill in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter in med. size saucepan. Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter until onions are transparent. Remove onions from pan and add soup and sour cream to the onions. Pour into greased casserole. Add cornbread stuffing mix to the pan with leftover butter; stir to coat stuffing mix and put on top of casserole. Bake at 300° for 25 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: granny's pies or puddings
directions: Make a paste with sugar, flour and water.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then add 4 cups boiling water and cook until thick. This basic recipe makes coconut, lemon or chocolate pies.
It also makes banana or pineapple pudding.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugars.
Cut in butter until it looks like course meal.
Take out 1/2 cup to save for topping.
To the rest add buttermilk, baking soda, egg and vanilla.
Blend well. Grease 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add 1/2 batter, top with 1/2 the topping.
Cover with the rest of the batter and the rest of the topping.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
(Until toothpick inserted in middle comes out dry.)

title: green bean bundles
directions: Take 10 green beans and wrap 1/2 slice bacon around them. Secure with toothpicks.
You will average 9 bundles per can.
For each can of green beans used you will need one mixture of butter, sugar and seasoning.
Pour over beans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, brown bacon more by turning oven up to 400° for about 5 minutes.

title: cinnamon and sugar snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl or plastic bag, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each tortilla into 6 or 8 wedges.
Place wedges in single layer on cookie sheets then spray wedges with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake 5 - 7 minutes or until wedges are light brown and crisp.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in covered container or plastic bag.

title: onion-corn bread casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet; cool.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Combine muffin mix, eggs, milk, corn and cayenne pepper in a bowl.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon onion mixture on top.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: waldorf red velvet cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Mix plain flour, salt, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add to mixture.
Blend in soda, then vinegar.
Don't beat; just blend.
Bake in four cake layer pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: raspberry cheese paska
directions: Strain the liquid from the raspberries and boil liquid with the 1/4 pound granulated sugar for approximately 5 minutes.
Cool and reserve to serve this with the Paska.
Remove the seeds from raspberries by putting through a sieve.
Cream the cream cheese with the sweet butter in electric beater.
Add sugar and cream well.
Lastly, add the raspberry pulp and cream well with the beater.
Line your form with cheesecloth and pour in the mixture. Freeze until 1 hour before you plain to serve.
Top with the sauce when you serve, if you want to, but not necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups and milk together.
Place in baking dish and top with stuffing,
prepared as directed on box.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and brown.

title: citrus cooler
directions: In saucepan, combine the sugar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over mint leaves in a bowl.
Cover.
Let steep for 10 to 20 minutes.
Strain.

title: banana pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well after each addition.
Mix baking soda with sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture; alternate with sour cream.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Blend in mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams.
Put clam liquid over vegetables and add water to cover.
Cook over low heat until tender.
In another pot, melt butter.
Add flour and half and half.
Stir frequently until smooth and thick.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Add clams and spices; simmer 1/2 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread top with 1/2 cup ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach jello
directions: Mix well. Let jell.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in dutch oven or roaster.
Bake covered at 250 degrees for 5-6 hours.
Check and add more V8 juice if stew looks dry.

title: forget-me-not cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add baking powder, gradually, and sugar while beating.
Beat until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans and butter.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Place in oven preheated to 350°.
Turn off immediately.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: seaside salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Add other ingredients.
Combine well and chill.

title: bean and bacon chowder
directions: Combine beans and water in large kettle; bring to boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Saute bacon and onion until lightly browned.
Add with fat to beans and simmer 1 hour.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer another 30 minutes.
Gradually add milk to flour, then add to soup.
Bring to gentle boil.

title: company chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and roll in Bisquick until they are coated evenly.
Place chicken breasts in Pyrex dish. Spoon the undiluted mushroom soup evenly over the chicken breasts.
Drain mushrooms and place over chicken breasts.
Fill empty mushroom can with white wine and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and serve over rice or noodles.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo until onion is tender.
Add soup, milk and Velveeta cheese (do not salt).
Cook on medium heat until cheese and soup are melted and creamy.
This recipe can be halved.

title: ham party rolls
directions: Put small pieces of ham and cheese into sliced rolls.
Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, poppy seed and onion. Spread on inside of each roll.
Place rolls in pans.
Brush remaining mixture over tops of rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: nana's coconut cookies(from 1939)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Mix in eggs well.
Add salt, baking powder, vanilla, flour and coconut.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut meat, potatoes, onions and carrots in bite size pieces. Place all ingredients in casserole. Stir to mix. Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 hours.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix dates, sugar, butter and well beaten egg in a large iron skillet.
Place over low heat and cook until dates are melted. Stir occasionally.
Turn off heat immediately and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well and let cool.
Make into small balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: coconut icing
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients not over 2 minutes.
Pour over beaten egg whites.
Beat about 10 minutes, then ice cake.

title: goulash
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onions in oil until tender.
Remove and reserve.
Combine paprika, salt and pepper and coat meat with these.
Brown meat in onion drippings.
Return onions to pot. Stir in tomato paste, water, garlic and remaining salt.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
If too thick, add more water. Garnish with sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: praline cookies
directions: Note:
This is good with coconut, too.

title: orange chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken; thicken butter with brown sugar and flour.
Add frozen orange juice and 1 can water.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Bake 1 hour at 325° covered. Garnish with orange and parsley (if desired).
Serve over rice.

title: country corn pudding
directions: Thaw corn in refrigerator.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Serves 10.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 prepared cake pans.
Bake 325° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and sausage stew
directions: Trim fat from beef. Cut beef into 3/4-inch cubes. Set aside. Place 1/2 cup flour in resealable plastic food storage bag. Add beef and seal the bag.

Shake bag to coat beef cubes with flour evenly on all sides. Place beef cubes in slow cooker. Add tomatoes with juice, sausage slices, diced potatoes, chopped leek, chopped onion, sliced celery, chicken broth and minced garlic.
Stir well. Cover slow cooker and cook on high 4 to 6 hours or on low 8 to 12 hours. (One hour before serving, turn slow cooker to high if on low setting.)

title: fruit salad(low-fat)
directions: Place all the fruit into a large
bowl.
Pour pineapple and its juice over all fruit; mix.
Add walnuts and celery, if desired.
Mix.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Place 8 crescent rolls in pie plate, forming a crust.
Spread 2 tablespoons mustard on crust.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onion, zucchini, salt and pepper (to taste).
Cook 10 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs in bowl and add 2 cups of cheese.
Stir together zucchini, eggs and cheese with seasonings.
Place in pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cover with foil and bake 10 minutes more until set.
Let stand a few minutes before slicing.
"Um good!"

title: very rich chocolate pie
directions: Melt together marshmallows, milk and chocolate chips.
Blend together and cool thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Spread beans in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Top with meat.
Sprinkle with chilies, onions, olives, then cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over all.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mound mashed avocado in center.
Top with sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot fudge sundaes
directions: For sauce, in a heavy saucepan, combine chocolate and 1/3 cup water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar and a dash of salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 8 minutes or until sugar is dissolved and mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In Dutch oven, bring veggies and water to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Add meat and bean soup. Heat thoroughly.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients with electric beater until creamy and pour over crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Refrigerate overnight.
Pour 1 can blueberry pie filling over cheesecake and cover with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O and dissolve.
(Put aside 1/4 cup of this for topping.)
Add crushed pineapple and strawberries (juice too).
Mix well and put in dish; let congeal.
Have cream cheese at room temperature and mix with confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add this and the 1/4 cup of Jell-O to Dream Whip for topping.
Spread on congealed mixture and top with nuts.

title: sugar-free brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, salt, 1/4 cup water and vanilla in mixer for 3 minutes.
Gradually add balance of water; mix 1 minute.
Pour batter into 10-inch pan sprayed with Pam (one 8-inch pan and one 8 x 4-inch pan can be used instead).
Sprinkle batter with almonds. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut bars in pan.
Makes 2 dozen (2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and
bake
in greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: ravioli stuffing
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in butter.
Add beef, pork and all the other ingredients.
Let stand.

title: cheese puffs
directions: In a bowl, combine cheese, cornstarch, spices and herbs.
Beat egg whites.
Slowly stir egg whites into cheese mixture.
Shape into small balls.
Roll balls into cracker crumbs and almond mixture.
Deep fry balls in hot oil, then drain on paper towels.

title: oven brown potatoes
directions: Clean and quarter baby red potatoes.
Combine butter and next 5 ingredients.
Pour butter mixture over potatoes, stirring to coat well.
Place potatoes in baking pan.
Sprinkle onions over the top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Remove wrappers from tamales and cut into thirds.
Combine tamales, hominy, sausages and soup.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
As soon as the dish comes out of the oven, sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add soups and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add enchilada sauce and heat.
Pour over Doritos in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 10 ounces grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: no bake lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Add tomato paste, sauce, mushrooms, garlic, basil, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and water.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Let Mozzarella melt over sauce.
Serve like spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: reception salad
directions: Mix jello with pineapple juice which has boiled.
When it begins to set, add ingredients.
Fold in whipped whipping cream. Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat after each. Alternate flour and whipping cream to mixture until all is used. Add vanilla flavor.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: impossible ham and vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Rinse beans under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly. Spread beans and ham in plate.
Beat cottage cheese, sour cream, margarine, eggs and baking mix until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high, stopping blender occasionally to scrape side, or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Arrange tomato slices on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6
to 8 servings.

title: ham, corn and potato chowder
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Melt butter; saute onion 5 minutes.
Add milk, ham, cream of mushroom soup and potatoes. Cook over medium heat about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cream-style corn, salt and peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in oleo.
Add cheese, rice, soup and broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with small can Pet milk.
Have your Cheez Whiz melted, then mix all together.

title: lillie's crispy bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in mixture of lime and water overnight. Mix until lime dissolves, rinse cucumbers and drain.
Slice cucumbers into 1/4 inch slices and return to large container.
Add onions.
Pour salt over all and mix well.
Cover with cubed or chipped ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain container.
In a large kettle, mix vinegar, sugar and spices, tied in a cheese cloth bag.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil.
Add onions and cucumbers and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pack into jars, remove spices and pour hot syrup into jars to within 1/2 inch of the top and seal.

title: dip
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread refried beans.
Stir together taco seasoning and sour cream.
Spread over beans. Layer onions and tomatoes; top with Cheddar cheese.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: seafood rice salad
directions: Combine ingredients and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: ground beef oven dinner
directions: Butter an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Lightly saute ground beef.
Spread meat evenly in dish.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and onion powder over the meat.
Cover generously with grated cheese. Add green beans and mushrooms that have been mixed with the soup. Top with Tater Tots; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In plastic bag, combine flour and pepper. Add chicken and shake to coat well.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise and ketchup.
Pour half evenly over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and turn. Cover with remaining mayonnaise mixture. Return to oven and bake another 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cooked apple dumplings
directions: Roll out; cut into squares.
Into each square, put one small, quartered apple.
Pinch dough all around it tight.
Drop into boiling water.
Let boil 1/2 hour.
Take out and serve hot, with sugar and cream.
Cook in heavy pot.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine and place in bottom of dish. Beat 1 cup milk, and both cream cheeses until smooth.
Add remaining milk and instant pudding.
Beat 1 minute on low speed only.
Do not overbeat!
Pour over crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Top with favorite pie filling and serve.

title: linguini alfredo
directions: Heat soup in pot.
Add milk and cheese.
Boil linguini; drain. Toss in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Pour on sauce and stir.

title: dinner casserole
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix peas and carrots and the remaining ingredients except for the potato chips in an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish or baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and slice.
Boil squash in pan along with 1/2 cup chopped onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes; drain.
Pour squash into casserole dish.
Mash lightly.
Add 1/2 of cornbread, egg, 1/2 melted butter and the rest of the onions.
Mix. Pour the other half of the cornbread crumbs on top of casserole. Pour remaining butter on top of cornbread.
Cook for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: skillet surprise candy
directions: Cook margarine, egg and dates for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add cereal, vanilla and nuts and mix well. Roll small round-shape pieces in coconut.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately to first mixture.
Add flavorings. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together and spread 1/2 to 2/3 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan (the batter will be very thick).
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with mixer and add sugar, beating until fluffy. Add vanilla and egg yolks; beat well.
Add flour a little at a time with a large spoon, mixing well.
Shape into walnut size balls. Flatten slightly with bottom of a glass if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
They will not be brown; only bottom edges should be slightly brown.

title: stuffed hot peppers
directions: Sauerkraut
seasoned with garlic powder.
Boil solution for five minutes.
Stuff peppers with kraut, and put in jars, cover with
solution.
Place in water bath canner, when water comes to a boil take out of canner.
Do not boil.
Wear rubber gloves.

title: chocolate meringue pie(with easy cooked meringue)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt in a heavy pan.
Mix well to remove lumps.
Gradually add milk and stir well.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil a minute or two, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks and add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in margarine and vanilla.
Immediately pour into a baked pastry shell.
Spread meringue over, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 425° for 7 or 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in potatoes, then mix eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Heat on top of stove until thickens. Put in buttered casserole and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Melt oleo.
Mix with pecans, corn flakes and brown sugar.
Pour on top of baked mixture.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir. Cut each biscuit into quarters, cutting almost but not all the way through the bottom.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture. Bake 15 minutes more or until biscuits are golden brown and filling is hot and bubbling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased broiler pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together in large buttered dish. Put crushed crackers and melted butter on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 325° to 350° oven.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions to make 1 gallon.
Layer the cucumbers and onions in glass jar.

title: savory broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package directions.
Drain water from the cooked broccoli.
Return broccoli to the pan and add the cream cheese which has been cut into small pieces.
After the cream cheese has melted, add the salt, mushroom soup and 1/2 can of the crushed onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the rest of the onions and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, shortening and milk.
Roll out.
Place apples down center of dough.
Fold dough over.
Cut in 1-inch thick slices. Place in buttered pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: dilly bean roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and horseradish.
Spread thin layer of cheese mixture on each piece of beef.
Roll up around a dilled green bean.

title: candied sweets
directions: Parboil potatoes 15 minutes.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise. Place in buttered baking dish.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour syrup over potatoes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut biscuits in half.
Melt butter and dip biscuits in butter and then cinnamon-sugar.
Place in pan in rows, just touching each other. Sprinkle leftover butter and cinnamon sugar on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk in small bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Combine whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and brown sugar in bowl; make a well in center. Combine cereal mixture, egg, oil, applesauce and lemon juice.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in grated carrot and raisins.
Spoon into lightly vegetable oil sprayed muffin pans (2/3 full).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips with condensed milk and butter; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture; spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours until firm. Remove from pan.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar and onion in blender. Drizzle oil into mixture while continuing to blend.
Add poppy seed and pepper.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: ginger sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line a 13 x 9 baking pan with foil and spray foil with cooking spray. In mixing bowl, mix flour, cornstarch, ginger, cinnamon, pepper and salt. In another bowl, beat butter until creamy. Add sugar and molasses, beating until smooth. Put flour mixture into butter mixture and beat until smooth. Spread into prepared pan. Sprinkle with ginger. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with coarse sugar; bake 10 minutes more. Cool in pan. Cut into thirds lengthwise, then crosswise into 12 (1-inch) strips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, zucchini and vanilla with a mixer.
Fold remaining ingredients, except nuts, into mix.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: maw maw byar's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish. In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are fine crumbs.
Add milk; stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Roll dough into a rectangle and sprinkle cinnamon over apples; then sprinkle apples over the dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edge of dough with water to seal.
Slice dough into 16 slices.
Pour sugar syrup over.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt oleo and Velveeta cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish. Stir cocoa and vanilla into oleo and cheese mixture.
Slowly mix powdered sugar into mixture.
Cover a large cooke sheet with aluminum foil.
Put margarine on hands, use hands to transfer fudge to cookie sheet, then smooth out.
Put cookie sheet in freezer for 15 minutes.
Remove and cut into squares.
Store in Tupperware. Must be kept in refrigerator.
You can add nuts and marshmallow at beginning.

title: spinach soup
directions: Mix water, bouillon cubes and milk.
Add onion, celery and spinach.
Bring to boiling.
Turn down to a simmer.
Melt margarine and mix with flour.
Mix well so there are no lumps. Add flour and margarine mixture to soup.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
This soup base may also be used with broccoli, mushrooms, celery or other combinations as well.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour and the next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in chilled margarine with a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk; stir until moist.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface; knead dough 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to a 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 11 minutes, or until golden.

title: aunt mary's fudge
directions: Batter an 8 x 8 pan.
Mix well sugar, cocoa and milk. Cook to a soft ball stage after it reaches soft ball stage. Add butter and vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Combine broccoli, eggs, mayonnaise, soup, onion, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 X 13 baking dish.
Arrange the chiles in a layer over the bottom of the dish.
Cover with the cheese.
Blend the eggs, salt, milk and Bisquick mix.
Pour over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Crush cornflakes in plastic bag.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then in cornflake crumbs.
Place foil on baking sheet.
Place chops on foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aloha bread
directions: Sift
all dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder).
Cream
butter,
sugar and eggs.	Blend well. Add
all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake
at 350° for 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into loaf.
(Freezes well.)

title: hash brown supreme
directions: Mix together hash browns, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, milk and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamed cabbage with cheese
directions: Shred the cabbage fine.
Cook in small amount of salted boiling water until tender but still crisp.
Drain well.
Place cabbage and cheese in layers in greased baking dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Stir in milk slowly; cook and stir until sauce comes to a boil.
Add salt, paprika, onion and parsley.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until crumbs are brown.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes(hamburger on a bun)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Add other ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Can be done in crock-pot.
Great after sports events or school activities.

title: summer cake
directions: Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
Let cool.

title: wildberry punch
directions: Combine all into large punchbowl.
Let sherbet melt before serving.

title: lemon yogurt bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add oil and sugar.
Cream well.
Add lemon yogurt and extract.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour in large Bundt pan at 350°.
Test with toothpick.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Beat well the oleo, sugar, vanilla and egg and add to the dry ingredients.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Drain maraschino cherries.
Press one cherry into the center of each dough ball. Cover with frosting and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: applesauce-ginger ale gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in applesauce.
Slowly pour ginger ale down the side of the bowl.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.
Chill overnight to congeal.
Serves 24.

title: lite chicken salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients, then blend well with mayonnaise and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in Dutch oven or large skillet. Add all other ingredients except spaghetti.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour then uncovered 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave oriental beef and tomato casserole
directions: In a deep quart microwave casserole dish, place beef.
Heat on full power 5 minutes or until meat is no longer red.
Drain excess liquid.
Add garlic, soy sauce, ginger, celery, onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Heat on full power 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In
a small custard cup, combine cornstarch and water to make a smooth paste.
Add cornstarch mixture to liquid in casserole.
Heat on full power 2 minutes until mixture is thickened and smooth.
Serves 4.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Wrap bacon around chestnuts.
Place in broiler until bacon is cooked.
Place cooked wraps in slow cooker.
Pour barbecue sauce over.
Heat and serve.
Great appetizer.

title: farm house sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Fill thoroughly greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in Pyrex oblong pan.
Add sliced potatoes, turning to coat both sides.
Sprinkle with 1 package mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° until tender.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and set aside.
Crumble cake; reserving 1/2 cup.
Place half of the remaining cake crumbs in the bottom of 4 1/2 or 5-quart trifle dish or decorative glass bowl.
Layer with half of the coffee, half of the pudding, half of the Cool Whip and half of the candy bars.
Repeat the layers of cake, coffee, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine remaining crushed candy bars with reserved cake crumbs; sprinkle over top. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours before serving. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: german cucumber salad
directions: Pare and slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak in lightly salted water for 1 1/2 hours.

title: berry delight
directions: Combine flour, butter, brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° in long Pyrex dish for 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes until light brown.
Cool, but remove enough crumbs to sprinkle on top of mixture.
Leave a good layer in dish.
In large bowl, beat frozen berries, sugar, egg whites, cream cheese, lemon juice and salt. Beat slowly and gradually increase to high speed.
Beat about 10 minutes, then fold in whipped topping.
Pour over crumbs and top with crumbs.
Freeze.
Can be served with berries on top.
(Can be made a day ahead.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until creamy.
Add sugars. Add next 5 ingredients.
Roll dough into balls the size of a quarter, then roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and push 1 Hershey Kiss down in top of cookies while hot.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook broccoli until done.
Chop up the chicken and then the broccoli.
Layer in a casserole dish. Mix in a bowl, soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Grate cheese and put on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: yummy yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 prepared 9-inch cake pans at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and ice with Icing.

title: parmesan bass fillets
directions: Heat
oven to 450°.
Cut fish into serving size pieces. Place margarine
in
a
x 9-inch baking pan.
Place pan in oven for 5 minutes to melt margarine.
Place fish in pan, skin side up. Sprinkle
with salt and pepper.
Bake for 5 minutes; turn. Sprinkle
with
lemon
juice
and white wine.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle
with
paprika.
Bake
until
fish flakes easily at thickest part, about 5 minutes.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Heat in saucepan over low heat until warm; do not boil.
This dressing can be used warm or cold but I always heat it anyway to blend the ingredients a little better.

title: pastry for double crust pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 3 to 4 tablespoons of water over mixture.
Gently toss with a fork. Add just enough water to hold mixture together.
Divide and form each half into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, flatten 1 ball of the dough with hands.
Roll from center to edge, forming a circle about 12 inches in diameter.
Wrap pastry around rolling pin.
Unroll onto pie plate, ease into plate being careful not to stretch.
Trim away beyond rim of the plate.
Roll remaining dough in same way.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Press muscadines, one at a time, to remove the pulp.
Boil the hulls in a small amount of water for 30 minutes or until tender. Cook the pulp and sugar for 15 minutes, then mash through a sieve to remove seeds.
Drain the hulls and add to pulp.
Mix lemon juice, flour and salt to a smooth paste.
Add to the pulp and hulls.
Stir in cinnamon and pour into the uncooked shell.

title: field pea jambalaya
directions: Heat the oil. Add smoked sausage and seasonings (cook a few minutes). Add 2 cups water and bring to a boil. Add a little Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour field peas with rice and water.
Lower heat, cover and cook about 25 minutes.

title: turkey breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wrap turkey and ingredients in 2 layers of foil.
Seal each layer with double foil fold.
Leave for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave overnight.
Do not open oven.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts. Shape dough into two rolls, each roll approximately 1 1/2-inches high, 2 1/2-inches wide and about 7-inches long.
Chill dough for several hours in refrigerator.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: garden good green beans
directions: Halve beans lengthwise.
Saute onion in margarine in saucepan until soft.
Stir in beans.
Toss until well coated.
Stir in seasonings, 1/4 cup water and bouillon cube, crushing bouillon with spoon until dissolved.
Cover.
Cook for 10 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dinosaur cookies
directions: Mix in a bowl.
Pour out.
Bake it in the oven at 10°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and confectioners sugar until smooth. Form into small balls the size of "buckeyes." Refrigerate balls.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and cook in heavy, oven-proof pan with cover.
When browned, remove and drain on paper towels. Saute onion and green pepper and cook for one minute.
Add rice and cook for 3 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover pot and place in oven.
Bake covered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: fat-free centerpiece coleslaw
directions: Place the shredded cabbage in a large mixing bowl.
Pour the juice from the pimentos over the cabbage.
Chop the pimentos.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Arrange the cabbage leaves in a large serving bowls.
Pour the coleslaw in the center of the leaves.
The salad should have the appearance of a freshly picked head of cabbage with coleslaw in the center.
Very attractive salad.
Serves 8.
Three-fourth cup serving:
calories 98.
Fat and cholesterol 0.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers.
Put 1 layer in punch bowl. Pour 1 package of pudding mix and let cool until set.
Then add drained fruit as needed.
Then add the other layer and repeat step with fruit.
Then add Cool Whip for topping.

title: white bean chicken chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, cumin, oregano, aniseed and red pepper and saute for 5 minutes. Push onion to one side of pan.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute 5 minutes.
Drain beans; reserve 1/2 cup bean liquid.
Add broth, beans, chilies, cream and reserved bean liquid to chicken.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until chicken is tender. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with cilantro on individual serving.
Can be prepared a day ahead and refrigerated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking or broiler pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: parmesan breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Divide dough into quarters.
Pat seams together, forming 4 rectangles.
Cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips.
Roll in Parmesan cheese, twist strips.
Bake on cookie sheet according to package directions.

title: sinful chocolate dessert
directions: Bake cake and tear into bite size pieces.
Prepare pudding according to package
Layer cake, pudding, nuts, candy and Cool Whip.
Make sure the top layer is Cool Whip.
Before final Cool Whip top, poke holes and pour Kahlua or Amaretto into holes.
