Save crumbs from candy bars to sprinkle on top.
Makes large container of dessert.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: cherry salad
directions: Thaw Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Boil rice, 6 cups milk, salt and butter together for approximately 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
In blender, place egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Add this blended mixture to cooked rice mixture and return to a full, rolling boil. Place in dish and add vanilla.
Fold in meringue from egg whites. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: polka dot nuggets
directions: Blend marshmallow cream and peanut butter in bowl.
Add cereal and candies; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls; place on waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs and blend in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and currants.
Stir into the zucchini mixture until well blended.
Divide batter into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes then turn out onto wire racks to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well together; coat ball with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: snack mix
directions: Boil all together.
Pour over warm party mix.
Stir every 15 minutes for 2 hours in 150° oven.
This can be made in 1/2 batches.

title: sugar-free birthday cake (uncooked)
directions: Grate or blend apples to fine consistency.
Chop dates.
Grind sunflower seeds finely in nut mill.
Add other ingredients.
Form mixture into cake shape.
Garnish with additional coconut or strawberries.
Refrigerate to set.
Slice before serving.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender; drain.
Meanwhile, put milk, mayonnaise, flour, salt, mustard, pepper and onion in blender and blend in baking dish.
Pour on sauce.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight for best results.

title: glorified macaroni
directions: Refrigerate oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Cook pasta and refrigerate overnight.
Drain juices from fruit and add 2 1/2 tablespoons flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cook until thick. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix all ingredients with Cool Whip.
Add maraschino cherries (cut up) for color.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces and spread in large bowl.
Layer with celery, green pepper, frozen peas and onions.
Frost with Miracle Whip. Sprinkle sugar on top of dressing.
Layer grated cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve any time up to 24 hours later.

title: lebkuchen cookies
directions: Heat first 7 ingredients through but not hot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix as regular cookies.
Let stand overnight. Roll out and cut with a knife.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until blended.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in pan of hot water and bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Rinse beans; place in Dutch oven with 4 cups cold water. Bring to boiling; simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add beef shank, ham hock, onion, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, thyme and dash of pepper.
Return to heat and bring to boiling. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bones; cut off meat and dice. Add meat, potatoes and carrots to soup. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs, salt, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla with a wooden spoon. Add apples, raisins and 1/2 cup of the nuts and blend. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt jane smith's bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Remove from heat. Add sugar, corn syrup and bourbon.
Mix in cookie crumbs and walnuts.
Form teaspoon amount into 1-inch balls.
Roll in fine granulated sugar. Ferment 48 to 72 hours in airtight container. Serve and enjoy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburg with Italian seasoning.
In a covered casserole dish, layer cooked hamburg, sliced potatoes, sliced onion and carrots.
Make as many layers as you wish, by adding more potatoes and carrots.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add garlic, parsley flakes, oregano, salt, tomatoes or juice, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Grease dish, layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Whip cream.
Mix sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Fold into cream. Spread cream mixture between crackers.
Cover top and sides with cream mixture.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, and molasses together.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar placed on waxed paper.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Crush crackers; mix chopped vegetables with meat and seasoning.
Stir in tomato paste and eggs.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Blend ingredients well. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poor boy stroganoff
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add soup, sour cream and onion.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over noodles or toast.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender.
When cool, alternate layers of carrots, green bell pepper rings and onion slices.
Make marinade of remaining ingredients, beating well until completely blended.
Pour mixture over vegetables and sit overnight in refrigerator.
Ready to serve.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ground beef, kidney beans, and onion and refrigerate.

title: all-in-one breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. In medium saucepan over low heat, bring milk to the boiling point. Slowly sprinkle in Cream of Wheat cereal, stirring constantly. Return to boiling point; reduce heat.
Stir until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 cup of cheese and mustard; stir until cheese melts.
Beat in eggs until well blended; stir in the sausage.
Spread into prepared pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage - apple balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix well in blender.
Pour in ice cream freezer.
Add whole milk to fill line.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Boil in double boiler, beating until thick.
When cool, mix in equal amount of Cool Whip.
This is good on fruit salad or Jell-O vegetable salad.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter. Add ground beef and brown. Cut cabbage into 1-inch squares. Add to beef mixture. Cook, covered, slowly until tender (about 10 minutes). Add sour cream and cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a casserole dish. Top with buttered toasted bread. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together good.
Grease a big bread pan with oil.
Pour in bread pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Eat hot with milk or butter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: spicy pasta
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, pepper, celery and garlic in a 12-inch skillet until meat is brown and vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili powder, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in pasta; heat through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: white trash
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Melt chocolate and drizzle over dry ingredients.
Combine thoroughly and place on large cookie sheet to dry.
Makes nice Christmas gifts in white "trash" bags tied with a festive ribbon and recipe attached.

title: patio sheet cake
directions: Mix butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add sugar.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Spread half of dough in bottom of a cookie sheet. Spread pie filling over dough.
Crumble remainder of dough on top, to cover pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and then 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Stir sugar and	flour
together in a large mixing bowl. Stir in	blackberries.
If using frozen berries, let partially thaw. Add lemon
juice.
Fill
pastry
lined 9-inch pie plate with blackberry	 mixture.
Dot
with
margarine.
Top	with remaining crust.
Flute
edges.
Cut	slits in top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes.
If using frozen berries, cover edge of pie with foil and bake 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: date cake
directions: Combine the dates, boiling water and soda; let stand until cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients with date mixture and pour into a 6 x 12-inch or a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball stage or 252° on candy thermometer, stirring often.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add gelatin and continue beating until egg whites form a peak. Slowly beat in the hot syrup mixture.
Continue beating until mixture will hold a shape.
Add nuts and drop quickly on waxed paper or pour into greased pan.

title: german chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare brownie layer:
Microwave chocolate in large bowl until melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.

title: mabel's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Combine squash, ground beef, onion, cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot pepper-onion relish
directions: Grind pepper with onions. Drain and put in vinegar mix. Simmer 20 minutes. Drain and pack in hot jars. Spoon hot vinegar to wet relish.
Seal jars.

title: nacho chips - cold
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; spread on a tray or in a clear glass bowl.
Top with rest of ingredients.
Serve with nacho chips.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in 2 large bowls.
Mix 1/2 pound nuts into each bowl.
In a 5-quart saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Pour half of syrup over each bowl of popcorn and stir to coat.
Turn coated popcorn into a large roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Remove from the oven and break apart while warm.
Cool. Store in airtight containers.
Yields 12 quarts.

title: oven chicken casserole *
directions: New method to cook old ham.
Soak ham (10 to 12 pounds) overnight; wash ham well.
Put in roaster, add 6 to 7 cups water (cold).
Put top on roaster tight, all vents closed.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Put ham in oven and cook ham for 15 minutes at 500°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix eggs and liquid.
Save 1/2 cup cheese for top.
In well-buttered casserole, layer zucchini, onions, crackers, pepper and cheese.
Repeat until all is used.
Pour egg mixture over top. Sprinkle cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lee's meatballs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Roll into very small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Pour 1 can of beef consomme over the cooked meatballs. Heat over very low heat and serve.
A crock-pot works great. Recipe easily doubles.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook and cool spinach according to package directions.
Add flour to grated cheese.
Cook pie shells 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch to prevent burning.
Combine milk, eggs, spinach, salt and pepper. Add cheese.
Put in 2 pastry shells and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: joyce's pudding cake
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, milk and almond extract until bubbly. Stir often.
Cut pound cake in slices.
Add pudding, candy pieces and almonds.
Repeat with cake layers.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: bunker hill gravy and beef chunks minute beef stroganoff
directions: Turn gravy and beef into skillet.
Heat slightly and remove beef chunks.
Add to gravy the onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Cover and simmer until onion is tender, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Cook beef in soups, adding 1/2 can of water approximately 3 hours or until tender.
Simmer slow in covered pan.
Serve over mound of rice.

title: wanda's holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; place juice in small saucepan.
Add sugar, flour and egg to juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Cool.
Combine pecans and fruit; add dressing, stirring well.
Chill before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cucumbers vinaigrette
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut into very thin slices.
Combine vinegar, sugar and water and pour over cucumbers.
Add 1 cut clove garlic and sprinkle with chopped fresh dill or dill weed. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove garlic before serving.

title: broccoli-mushroom casserole
directions: Place broccoli in large saucepan with 1 inch of water.
Bring to a boil, cover and steam for 5 minutes.
Drain and chop coarsely. Heat 3 tablespoons butter in skillet, add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes, stirring.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 8 tablespoons butter, onion, mushrooms, half and half, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and eggs.
Mix all.
Add 1 cup cheese and 1 1/2 cups Ritz crackers.
Mix well and scrape mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and crackers on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: spicy crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in greased shallow baking dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spoon into greased 1-quart baking dish and cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Fold together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
At 400°, bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: granny's mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to the package directions. Just before taking the vegetables off, add celery and onions. Let stand for a few minutes. Drain well. Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese. Pour into a greased casserole.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add enough hot water to make dough stick together.
Shape into biscuit size patties and roll out thin.
Cook on hot griddle until brown, about 2 minutes on 1 side and 1 minute on the other side.
Used for burritos:
Fill with bean dip and cheese or meat filling.
Roll up and bake until cheese melts (covered).

title: fried corn
directions: After corn is cut from the ears, put in pot with Crisco, on medium heat, stirring to keep from sticking, for ten minutes.
Add flour; cook for 10 minutes longer, then add water.
Simmer and season to desired taste for 25 minutes longer.

title: low calorie company casserole
directions: In pan, mix cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and broth until smooth.
Add margarine and onion, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute or until thick. Stir in chicken, green pepper, parsley and cooked rice.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil shells according to package and drain.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Serves 20.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 3-quart casserole, combine beans, catsup, molasses, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with French fried onions; bake an additional 5 minutes or until onions are deep golden brown.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: barbecue sauce(for crock-pot use)
directions: Mix and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in jar in refrigerator until ready to use.
Excellent over pork in crock-pot.

title: frittata di zucchini or mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix eggs and Bisquick. Stir other ingredients.
Pour in pan and bake 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cranberry and orange relish
directions: Cut unpeeled orange into eighths.
Place cranberries and sugar in food processor or grind.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain off excess water. Melt cheese and margarine in bowl.
Stir until smooth.
(I do this in microwave.)
Stir melted cheese mixture and crackers into broccoli.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
If desired, sprinkle some of the crushed crackers on top.
Dot with butter and bake in a 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be easily cut in half. Serves 12.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with chopped onions.
Mix mushroom soup and milk until mixture is creamy.
Pour over onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with layer of Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into pieces and chop onion.
Cover both with water in a saucepan and
cook until tender.
Drain and salt to taste. Mash mixture and mix
with
cup mayonnaise, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and
egg.
Pour
into
greased
casserole dish. Melt butter and mix
with herb stuffing.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can beans into bottom of greased pan.
Combine sugar and mustard; sprinkle half of mixture over beans.
Sprinkle onion. Top with remaining beans.
Sprinkle rest of sugar-mustard mixture, chopped bacon and catsup over beans.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: connie's best punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in hot water.
Pour into gallon jug.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Finish filling jug with cold water; shake well.

title: amalene tucker's party paradise refrigerator cake
directions: Grease a large pan, 10 x 15-inch with butter.
Arrange in layers as follows.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples, fill pan almost full. Pour water over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Crumble the flour, oleo and brown sugar together; put over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Score top of ham with diamond-shape and put 1 clove into each diamond.
In saucepan over low heat mix bourbon, sherry and ginger.
Heat through, do not boil.
Turn off heat and pour half of mixture over ham, put into roasting pan and pop into oven.
Cook at 400° first hour.
Turn oven down to 350° for 1 hour, then turn oven to 250° for 2 hours, basting every 15 minutes (keep roaster cover on).
To the ingredients remaining in saucepan, put whole jar of marmalade and bring to slow low heat. Remove cloves and throw away.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top of ham and carefully pour marmalade mixture over the ham trying to keep marmalade on top of ham (this is your glaze).
Turn oven up to 350° for 1/2 hour.
It's done!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on high for 4 hours (in crock-pot) with lid on.
Remove lid and cook for 4 more hours, stirring often.
May need to turn it down to low when it is as thick as you like.
Can use 8 ounces red hots candy instead of cinnamon.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Trim just the stems and tips from fresh green beans.
Use a jar that the beans will stand up in.
Put beans in saucepan with just enough water to half cover beans.
(Don't use aluminum, it will darken beans.)
Bring to a boil and simmer partly covered for 5 to 7 minutes.
Beans should be hot through, but crunchy.
Put beans in jar.
Use cooking liquid to half fill jar.
Add onion, sliced and separated into rings, 1/2 teaspoon salt and Tabasco.
Fill jar to top with cider vinegar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator, then enjoy.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Put drained spaghetti in big bowl.
Chop all vegetables and add to spaghetti. Pour in bottle and package of salad dressing. Stir.
Can sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour or 2.
Mix other ingredients well and add to sauerkraut.
Heat Wesson oil and vinegar.
Pour over the sauerkraut mixture.

title: pineapple sauce
directions: Drain pineapple, saving the juice.
Add lemon juice to pineapple juice.
In heavy saucepan, stir together cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually add pineapple juice.
Mix until smooth. Place over medium heat and cook until mixture thickens and boils. Boil about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add 6 drops of food coloring and vanilla.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Excellent on angel food cake.

title: bearsville fruit pizza
directions: Pat dough into large jelly roll pan.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and blend with sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled dough.
Arrange fresh or canned fruit on top.

title: fancy rice dish
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in butter, using Dutch oven. Add chicken broth, rice, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Stir in carrots and cook additional 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and butter; cook.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle over top.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° until firm. Sprinkle cheese on top after casserole is done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place milk, rice, sugar mixture in a double boiler.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice gets soft.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of sprayed baking dish.
Cook sausage. Layer bread, cheese, sausage and mushrooms.
Mix eggs, milk, chillies and salt.
Pour liquid over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Using electric mixer, mix all ingredients until dough becomes heavy. Then knead by hand. Roll teaspoon of dough in small balls. Press with fork crisscross. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Saute bacon and onions slowly until onions are soft; drain off fat.
Combine bacon and onions with beans, mustard, pineapple, chili sauce and salt.
Put into a casserole or bean pot (about 1 1/2-quart size).
Cover and bake in a very slow oven, 275°, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: granny's chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice according to directions.
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken, skin side down, over rice.
Mix soups in saucepan and heat.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Place in oven at 350°.
Cook until chicken is done.

title: pineapple-raisin sauce
directions: Mix all, except cornstarch and water; bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir into mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Good with ham or other meats.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add scalded milk gradually, stirring constantly to obtain a smooth paste.
Add well beaten egg yolks and cook in a double boiler for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into the pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: grilling herb mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a jar; seal tightly. Store in a cool, dry place.

title: aunt maxine wyckoff's peanut butter candy
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in electric skillet.
Heat to 280°. Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Pour into 8-inch buttered pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill. Add 7-Up before serving.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder together; add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat dredged berries in remaining flour. Fold into mixture gently.
Pour mixture into 10-inch buttered and sugar coated Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together corn bread mix, salt and baking powder.
Beat in eggs, oil and corn; add onion, cheese and peppers.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center is clean.

title: lychee-longan-mandarin nectar
directions: Puree each fruit in its own juice.
Combine the fruit purees in a container, refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve over ice.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In a large bowl combine milk and juice, blend well. Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. Fold into cream mixture and pour into pie shell and chill.

title: chokecherry jelly
directions: Mix altogether and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Skim off the jell.
Put in clean, hot jelly jars.
Pour melted wax over top and seal with lids.

title: fish baramundi macadamia
directions: *To Clarify Butter:
Melt slowly over low heat 1/4 pound (1 stick) of butter in frying pan.
As white foam and additives to butter (such as salt) rise to top, skim off top and dispose.
What is remaining in pan is "clarified butter."
The clear/clarified butter is less likely to burn and overbrown the fish before it is cooked through to the middle of the fillet.

title: sylvia's spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and pepper in a little oil. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
When onion begins to brown, add sausage and hamburger.
When hamburger and sausage are brown, add the can of crushed tomatoes.
Cook on low heat for approximately 1 hour.
After 1/2 hour, add sugar.
Make sure mixture is bubbling; stir frequently.
After hour has passed, add the tomato paste and 4 cans water; stir mixture together.
Cook and stir at least 4 hours, or transfer to crock-pot and let simmer on low all night.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix gelatin with cream cheese and coconut.
Roll into marble-size balls.
Roll each ball in sugar.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell; chill.
Combine milk, Hershey bar and marshmallows in pan over low heat.
Stir frequently until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Cool in refrigerator.
Fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Spoon mixture into pie shell; chill until set.
Frost with remaining whipped cream. Sprinkle chocolate sprinkles or shaved chocolate over top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Carnation milk.
Fill with homogenized milk and vanilla.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; beat in marshmallows, salt and almond flavoring. Add powdered sugar gradually, mixing well after each addition. Turn out on hard surface sprinkled with powdered sugar and knead until smooth, working in extra powdered sugar if mixing becomes too sticky. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: oh so good salad
directions: Note:
Brown the noodles and the almonds, then add the sesame seeds.
Use a heavy pan for the best results.

title: blueberry peach pie
directions: Heat water, sugar and cornstarch in pan over medium heat until it boils. Boil for one minute stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add Jello to cornstarch mixture. Let that cool to the side. Toss fruit with cornstarch mixture. Place in pie crust. Chill one hour. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch meringue pie
directions: Mix
sugar, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.	Add margarine and vanilla when you remove
from
stove.
Pour	in
baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: tarheel cracklin cornbread
directions: Stir all together and pour into greased cast-iron frypan.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peacon fingers
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients; mix thoroughly. Mold into small shaped fingers. Bake 325 degrees for 20 minutes let cool, then roll in confectioner's sugar.

title: hopple popple
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients except for eggs, in a shallow baking dish.
Pour eggs over ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with all types of veggies.

title: crabmeat fondue appetizer
directions: Whip cream cheese and butter together.
Stir in soup; dump in crabmeat.
Heat in fondue pot or bake in oven; but it should be served hot.

title: sour cream meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into meatballs and bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Prepare gravy and pour over meatballs.
Serve in crock-pot or other heated container.

title: broiled mackerel
directions: Mix.
Keep basting as broiling.
Garnish with parsley.
A salad and white wine complements this meal.

title: mocha pudding cake
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in water.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large mixer bowl; add coffee.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Top with coffee glaze, if desired.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cooked through.
May serve hot or add cold to salads.
Serves 4.
Each serving contains 29 calories, 9 g protein, 0 g fat, 0 mg chol. and 42 mg sodium.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix the brown sugar, shortening and egg together.
Cream well. If using melted chocolate, add it now.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) alternately with the milk.
Add the vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
While cookies are warm, frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: orange swizzle
directions: Reconstitute orange juice with ginger ale.
Pour over crushed ice.
Serve with an orange slice and cherry on each swizzle stick.

title: beef tips over noodles
directions: Toss flour, salt and pepper with beef cubes.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Combine beef broth, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over beef and vegetables; stir well.
Cover and cook on very low heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
(May also be cooked in a crock-pot for 7 to 12 hours.)
Before serving, turn up heat.
Make smooth paste from wine or water and flour and add to meat.
Stir well and let thicken.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Wash and dry eggplant; remove stems.
Leave eggplant whole and unpeeled.
Make a slit the length of each eggplant only to the center, not completely through the other side.
In each slit, drizzle 1 tablespoon olive oil and season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Gently press eggplant together and rub completely with olive oil. Rub an 11 x 7-inch baking dish with olive oil.
Place eggplant in dish. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: recipe for play dough
directions: In heavy aluminum saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
(May add a few drops of oil of wintergreen, cloves or cinnamon to give a more pleasant aroma.) Knead slightly, almost immediately.
Store in an airtight container.
Has a pleasing texture.

title: macaroni and cheese(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine milk, flour, margarine and salt to make a white sauce. Turn to low heat and add grated cheese, stirring constantly. Cook until cheese has melted and sauce boils.
Remove from heat. Alternate layers of macaroni and cheese sauce in nonstick baking dish and bake at 375° until mixture bubbles.
Makes 6 servings. One cup equals 1 bread and 1 meat.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen lemonade concentrate and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruit. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm (approximately 4 hours).
Unmold and slice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brownie-mint sundae squares
directions: Preheat oven.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Spoon batter into a foil-lined greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake as directed.
Cool thoroughly.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together and let stand for 2 hours.
Ready to eat.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Prepare pie.
Mix softened butter, sugar and corn meal.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add pineapple and coconut and mix well.
Spoon mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 to 40 minutes until center is firm.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Combine chicken, cream of mushroom soup, milk and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Spread 3/4 cup potato chips on bottom of greased 1-quart casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Cover with remaining chips and sprinkle with cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add soups, tomatoes and chicken to onions and bell pepper.
Bake in long baking dish. Lay Doritos on bottom of dish.
Add 1/2 mixture, grated cheese and add to top of this mixture a little chili powder.
Repeat again and cover with foil.
Bake in oven about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: hideg meggyleves(cold sour cherry soup)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the water, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil.
Add the cherries.
Partially cover and simmer over low heat for 35 to 40 minutes if the cherries are fresh or 10 minutes if they are canned.
Remove the cinnamon stick.

title: spanish chili
directions: Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Add all other ingredients. Stir and bring to bubbling.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Cook 8 to 12 hours on low heat.

title: goof-proof fudge(microwave)
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Microwave on High 2 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir vigorously until blended.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour or freeze 20 minutes.
Cut into pieces.

title: wiener bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
In large casserole dish combine baked beans, ground beef, hot dogs and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover.
Heat in microwave or in oven at 350° until heated through. You may also add chili powder, barbecue sauce or any other type of spice.

title: instant oatmeal
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor.
Pulse several times to cut up oats.
Store in tightly covered container.
To prepare, put equal parts oatmeal mix and water or milk in microwavable dish. Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Add more milk or water to get desired consistency.
Yields 1 serving.

title: a stir-fry dish
directions: Cut raw chicken breasts in cubes.
Add peas and broccoli flowerets
that have been blanched in boiling, salted water for 2 minutes; drain.
Add about 1 cup cashew nuts.
Stir all of these until
they are coated with oil and are tender-crisp (about 3 minutes).
Add
a sauce of soy sauce, rice, wine and cornstarch. Blend all together and serve.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with 4 ounces grated cheese, 8 ounces dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Crunch and add 1/2 medium bag of Doritos.
Slice and add large avocado.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together.
Add well beaten eggs. Dissolve ammonia in warm milk.
Add lemon and stir in enough flour to make very stiff.
Knead well; roll thin and cut as desired. Bake about 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cabbage and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in large saucepot in cold water to cover. Soak 6 hours.
Drain.
In same pot, combine beans, ham hock, garlic, onion, rosemary and 8 cups of water.
Bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 more hour.

title: broccoli-ham dish
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Spoon rice into a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole.
Place broccoli over rice.
Melt butter; pour 2 tablespoons over crumbs and set aside.
In remaining butter, saute onion until soft.
Add flour and salt and cook until bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thick.
Add ham and heat.
Pour over rice and broccoli.
Put crumbs over top; heat.

title: leon style ribs
directions: Generously sprinkle ribs on both sides with seasoned salt. Stand several hours.
Mix remaining ingredients in medium saucepan. Heat to boil, simmer, uncovered 30 minutes.

title: smoothies
directions: Put 2 cups fruit (ex. strawberries) in blender.
Chop until pureed.
Add 2 to 3 cups ice cubes.
Blend until ice is slushy. Add sugar to taste.
Blend again.
Pour into tall glass.
Tastes great!
Be creative.
Try peaches, pineapple, watermelon or even applesauce.
Add a little vanilla ice cream with applesauce.

title: blueberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Spoon in sour cream and blend. Fold in pie filling.
Then pour in mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press in pie pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours.
Spread remaining topping over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or nuts.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased pie pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: fix ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brush top of mixture with melted butter.
Bake immediately or cover and refrigerate.
If refrigerated, let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: stove top quick bread
directions: Place a large skillet over medium heat (preheat skillet).
Mix all ingredients.
Turn into an 8-inch ring mold.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Cover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
After 15 minutes, slip lid off a little to let steam escape.

title: italian casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste; simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Spoon into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place near outer edge, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese in center.
Brush biscuits with butter; sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are lightly brown.

title: french meat pie
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium.
Saute onion until tender. Remove and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together.
Drain. Combine onion, meat, potatoes and seasonings.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Make slits on top crust.
Brush with egg and bake in 375° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream Psalms 55:21.
Gradually add Jeremiah 6:20.
Cream together until fluffy.
Add Jeremiah 17:11 and beat thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with Lamentations 4:7.
Add flavoring.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in greased pan.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: oboe player's casserole(original obtained from fellow oboe player in lima symphony.)
directions: Cook beans and broccoli together about 8 minutes.
Drain. Stir together with next 4 ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish. Mix melted margarine with approximately 3 cups Rice Krispies. Sprinkle over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
(May need to cover part of time.)

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Boil water; add jello to dissolve.
Add lemon juice. Refrigerate to cool.
Chill milk.
Blend cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Pour milk in bowl.
Whip until bubbled up, slightly thick.
Fold into jello and cheese mixture.
Chill until set (preferably overnight).

title: nacho party dip
directions: Fry onions and hamburg.
Mix cream cheese and taco seasoning; spread in deep dish.
Pour picante sauce on top, then layer lettuce, tomato, hamburg, onions, scallions and cheese.
Add tortilla chips.

title: potato filling
directions: Mix well, combine with mashed potatoes.
Put in 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix all wet ingredients, now mix together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch round pans, that have been oiled and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; pour off grease.
Boil macaroni in separate pan while cooking ground beef.
Lower heat on ground beef to low.
Add milk and cheese.
Cover pan to allow cheese to melt.
When macaroni is done to your preference, add to ground beef and cheese.
Stir together so cheese coats everything.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in water.
Blend in flour.
Knead 15 to 18 times.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Cut into 4 to 6 pieces and shape into pretzels.
Place onto foil-lined cookie sheet and brush with egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: little river punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, sherbet and ginger ale in pitcher or punch bowl.
Serve with ice.

title: zucchini bread #3
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon onto waxed paper.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until well mixed.
Stir in the flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: white chocolate fantasy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Melt white chocolate in a double boiler over hot water or in microwave. Pour melted chocolate into large bowl, and cream together with butter and sugar using an electric mixer. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool
for 15 minutes then remove from pans and cool on a wire rack. Cool completely before frosting.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, beans and taco seasoning.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Eat with chips (tortilla).

title: chocolate pie
directions: This meringue will not be runny.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish with butter.
Mix all other ingredients together with spoon.
Pour into casserole, dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, nuts and drained cherries.
Pour into 2 ungreased 9 x 5 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Place onion and butter in baking dish.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese melts and potatoes are tender, stirring 3 to 4 times during cooking.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and microwave 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve 2 tablespoons of yeast in 1/2 cup very warm water (not hot).
Set aside.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine first six ingredients and beat until smooth with mixer. Spread onto 12-inch platter.
Spread chili sauce over cream cheese, leaving a border of cheese mixture (looks like a pizza).
Sprinkle crab meat on top.
Dip with crackers.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine rice and French dressing; cool to room temperature. Mix mayonnaise, onion and seasonings.
Place celery and peas in large mixing bowl; pour in mayonnaise mixture.
Add rice mixture, toss lightly with fork.
Chill salad well.
Drain and chill shrimp. Add shrimp to salad just before serving.
Turn salad into lettuce lined bowl.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together; season with salt, pepper and onion.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, pumpkin and spices.
Mix for 1 minute at low speed.
Pour into 9-inch prebaked shell and chill. Serve with lite Cool Whip.

title: mock apricot jam
directions: Combine zucchini and water.
Boil 6 minutes.
Add lemon juice, sugar and pineapple.
Boil 6 minutes.
Add the gelatin and boil 6 minutes more.
Fill jam jars.
Leave 1/2-inch room for expansion. Freeze jam.
After opening jar, jam needs to be refrigerated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all the ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for both soups. Shape into meatballs size of your choice. Cook until brown on all sides. Use the drippings for the gravy and add both of the soups.

title: french market sandwiches
directions: Slice croissants in half.
Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed and onion together and spread on croissants.
Top with 2 1/2 ounces ham and a slice of cheese.
Put together; cover with foil and warm in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: *deviled swiss steak
directions: Mix mustard and flour.
Pound into the steak.
It takes punishment and rewards you with tenderness!
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in a little cooking oil.
Place in a small roaster.
Pour over it the remaining ingredients, which have been mixed together.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix together the Jell-O and cherries.
Let set until firm. Beat Dream Whip, cream, sugar and vanilla together and top Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass pan, layer frozen hash browns to cover bottom; salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with fried onion rings.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bagels
directions: In a large bowl combine yeast and 1 3/4 cups flour, water, sugar and salt.
Beat at low speed 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl often.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in enough of rest of flour for stiff dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Cut into 12 portions, shape and let rest 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, add 1 tablespoon sugar to 1 gallon water and bring to boil.
Cook bagels 7 minutes in simmering water, turning once.
Bake at 375° on ungreased pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not use cast-iron pans or sheets, the bagels will stick.

title: fresh fruit malt-year round
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
You may need to add more orange juice if too thick or a little more fruit if too thin.
Serves 2.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken breast with water and boil until done.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients (reserve 1 cup of stuffing mix dry to sprinkle on casserole).
Mix ingredients well.
Add 1 cup of water if needed.

title: new bedford's "most historic" syrian nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart mixing bowl, place the taco seasoning.
Add oil and blend thoroughly.
Keep this mixture well blended while following next step.
On two layers of paper toweling, place one pita half, inside up.
Using a pastry brush, paint generously with seasoned oil.
Place another pita on top, inside down.
Roll vigorously with rolling pin.
Both pitas should end up equally coated.

title: corned beef pie
directions: Steam or boil peeled potatoes until soft.
In large bowl roughly chop up potatoes and grate onion into them.
Add crumbled corned beef and also salt and pepper to taste.
Place pie shell on bottom of pie dish and mold.
Then add the meat mixture.
Top with upper pie shell and trim edges of crust.
Make 2 to 3 slits in top of pie with a knife to vent.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown crust.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Lightly bake pie crust.
Mix all ingredients and pour into cooled pie shells.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, longer if possible, before serving.

title: sausage bites
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly; drain and set aside.
Mix eggs with cottage cheese, chives, pepper and cheese.
Set aside. Divide each roll into 8 sections.
Thinly roll each section and press into greased miniature muffin tin cups.
Add sausage and top with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: In a large skillet briefly saute garlic in the olive oil on medium-high.
Add carrots and cook 3 minutes.
Add onions and continue cooking and stirring often.
Add broccoli stalks and water.
Cover; simmer about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, broccoli flowerets, mushrooms and seasonings.
Stir well; cover and continue to cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato wedges and cook briefly.
Serve immediately.
Delicious over rice.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter both sides of bread and cut off crusts.
Place 8 slices of bread in the pan, forming a crust. Combine chicken, eggs, olives, mushrooms and mayonnaise together. Spoon over bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Heat deep fat to 380°.
Slice onions; separate into rings. Put remaining ingredients in blender; whip until smooth.
Dip onion rings into batter; drip excess from rings and drop into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Blend jello with boiling water until smooth and well dissolved. Add vanilla ice cream.
Stir ice cream until dissolved.
Blend in peppermint extract and semi-sweet chocolate that has been chopped in small pieces.
Pour into pan and chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: kendra's fruit salad
directions: Cook puddings. Mix together. Chill. Cut fruit into bite-sized chunks. Put fruit and nuts in dish. Add puddings until all fruit is coated. Chill and serve.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green peppers; drain. Add cooked noodles and corn. Mix and place in 4-quart casserole dish. Combine soup and water; pour over mixture. Top with bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook the pasta in salted water; do not undercook.
Drain and generously coat with cooking oil.
Mix all remaining ingredients together; add to pasta (best if marinated at least overnight).

title: quick quesadillas
directions: Place tortilla on microwavable plate. Arrange cheese slices on tortilla without overlapping. Fold tortilla in half. Cover. Microwave on high 25 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted. Let stand, covered one minute or until cool enough to eat. Fold in half again.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift sugar and measure out 3 cups. Measure 1 cup Crisco all vegetable shortening. Add sugar gradually to the Crisco in an electric mixer and cream thoroughly. Add one egg at a time and beat thoroughly until 6 eggs have been beaten in thoroughly. Sift cake flour once and measure out 3 cups. Add baking soda and salt and sift again. Gradually add the flour mix into the batter mix. Add flavoring and sour cream. Mix well. Bake in a tube pan, well-greased and lightly floured, for 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: spice apple bars
directions: Cream sugar, butter, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Spread into a well-greased and floured (8-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Combine with tomatoes, onion, artichoke hearts, black olives, garlic powder, salad dressing, basil, onion, salt and parsley, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Drain well and serve on spinach or endive.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Combine butter and preserves.
Beat at low speed of an electric mixer 1 minute or until mixed well.
Cover and chill. Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with croissants.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: delicious chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle liberally with soy sauce and pepper. Place in baking pan and cover with foil. Let marinate for about 1 hour and place in a 400° oven for about 2 hours, depending on size. Do not add salt as the soy sauce is salty. It makes delicious gravy.

title: pistachio whip
directions: In a large bowl, mix Cool Whip, oranges, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over Cool Whip mixture and stir to blend all ingredients.
Add chopped nuts if desired.
Chill for at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: pina colada cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl, stir cream cheese with a spoon until soft. Add dry pudding mix, dry milk and pineapple with juice.
Mix well. Blend in 1 tsp. coconut extract, rum extract and 1/4 cup Cool Whip. Spread mixture evenly into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes. In a small bowl, combine remaining 3/4 cup Cool Whip and 1/2 tsp. coconut extract.
Spread mixture evenly over cheesecake filling. Sprinkle coconut evenly over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8. 233 calories per serving (7 grams fat).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese and allow cheese and margarine to come to room temperature.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually.
Roll into small rolls.
Chill and slice 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies can be topped with a pecan half before baking.

title: pie crust for fried tarts
directions: Season to taste with 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Follow Solomon's prescription for a good boy in Proverbs 23:14 and bake.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Skin and slice tomatoes, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell, sprinkle with the 2 Tbsp. brown sugar and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Cover with top crust and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: loaf bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, water and salt; cool.
Into measuring cup, put 1 teaspoon sugar, yeast and warm water; stir.
Let rise to top of cup while first mixture cools to lukewarm.
Combine the 2 mixtures in a bowl.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Stir until as stiff as you can handle.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Make out in rolls or 2 loaves.
Let loaves rise again for about 2 hours.
Put in greased pans and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in Pyrex pie plate.
Top with slivered almonds and paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a shallow casserole dish.
Make 5 cuts partially through loaf of Spam.
Place in loaf dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cream cheese and Cheddar cheese to room temperature. Combine all ingredients except almonds, using the milk sparingly, if at all.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Wrap and chill. Roll in almonds before serving with hearty wheat crackers.
Adjust to taste.

title: chuck-wagon beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain and add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: wild rice and cranberry salad
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on the package and combine remaining ingredients. Add salad dressing and chill 2 hours.
Add peanuts just before serving.

title: pumpkin dessert bread
directions: Mix sugars, pumpkin and oil. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Grease and sugar or flour pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May use topping on hot bread.

title: snow peas
directions: Combine all ingredients except peas. Cover and chill 3 hours or overnight.
Rinse peas in cold water. Blanch in boiling water 1 minute. Drain and place blanched peas into ice water.
Pat dry. Slit curved edge of pea to 1/2-inch and fill with cream cheese filling.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown beef with mushrooms, garlic and seasonings. Add spinach, cook only until spinach is thawed. Stir in soup and sour cream. Pour into casserole dish, top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until cheese is browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix herb stuffing.
Divide in half and mix soup and sour cream with 1/2 of stuffing mix and all other ingredients. Place in buttered baking dish.
Spread the last half of the herb stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix.
Add cocoa, flour, and vanilla.
Pour into 9 inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For meat loaves, combine first seven ingredients in large bowl; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape meat mixture into eight 3 x 2-inch loaves.
Place in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until centers of meat loaves are no longer pink.

title: tortillas
directions: First you make it round. Cook it in the pan for 4 to 5 minutes. Turn it twice and roll it so it doesn't burn. Take if off and you eat it with tea in the morning.

title: venison chili(hunter's delight)
directions: Brown venison.
Add remaining ingredients and enough water to cover; simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Best when reheated.
The trick is in the vinegar.
Use 1 tablespoon vinegar with all venison roasts, chops, burgers, etc.; it takes all the wild smell away.
You can freeze this in Ziploc bags for a later date.

title: holiday yams
directions: Mix butter, sugar, nutmeg and pecans in skillet.
Cook until it thickens.
After it thickens, put on top of sweet potatoes. Bake until sweet potatoes are done, then add pineapple and marshmallows.
Put in the oven for another 5 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, add all fruits and nuts.
Melt marshmallows in saucepan with milk.
Heat and pour over fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Pack into 3 loaf pans, lined with freezer paper.
Will keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: easy raspberry jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water in an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Add ice cubes and stir until melted.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, both sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: almond bars
directions: Place almond bark in top of double boiler. If slab type bark is used, cut into chunks. Chips do not need to be cut.
Place over hot water and melt slowly over low heat until bark is melted. Don't let water boil and don't let top touch water.
Stir in peanut butter when bark is melted. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool until firm. Cut into bars.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water overnight, or simmer 2 minutes and let soak 1 hour.
Add ham, onion and seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer 40 minutes.
If too thick, add more water.

title: hawaiian baked chicken
directions: In 1/4 cup melted butter, quickly brown the chicken on both sides.
Place in a single layer in a baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine juices, sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Stir in fruit.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake 15 minutes longer, until chicken is tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, jello, sugar and water to a boil. Boil until thickens. Take off heat and cool. Pour in fresh strawberries, and pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator until filling congeals.

title: green cabbage and egg noodles
directions: Cook noodles in salted, boiling water and drain.
Melt butter in skillet, add onion and saute.
Add cabbage, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until cabbage is of desired tenderness (approximately 10 minutes).
Add noodles and tomatoes, toss mixture until extremely hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Use square casserole dish.
Put layer of asparagus, then layer of mushroom soup. Sprinkle over this the pecans, chopped.
Add another layer of each and asparagus juice.
Top with cornflakes. Sprinkle on grated cheese. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: May be served hot or
cold.
If
served hot, add 3 cups fine bread crumbs and
bake
in	moderate
oven	until hot and bubbly.

title: mini pizza
directions: Spread toasted muffins with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and cheese.
Top with meat.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary mixer or at lowest speed of an electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread on cake at once.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes (partially cook, not too soft).
Cool and grate. Melt butter in chicken soup; cool.
Blend in sour cream and green onions.
Add to potatoes; season.
Add grated cheese.
Put in casserole and sprinkle some grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Core and peel apples.
Slice each apple into pieces and place in large bowl.
Add lemon juice, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Toss and toss and toss and toss and toss.
Prepare pie crust and place first one loosely in a 9 inch pie pan.
Trim edges leaving about 1/4 inch around the edge.
Place apples in pie shell. Prepare second pie shell (when rolling it out, roll out wider than the pie pan).
Place pie shell over apples and trim, leaving a little more than a 1/4 inch hanging over.
Join the edges together by pinching and tucking them together.
Make a design on top, brush milk on top and sprinkle on sugar.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and orange jello.
Mix all together and chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until done.

title: american fruit tart
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in 10-inch tart pan or quiche dish (9-inch pie plate may be substituted).
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Mixture will be thick. Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: cheesy fish bake
directions: Thaw fish. Cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together process cheese spread and milk.
Stir in peas, rice, dill weed and fish.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Stir once or twice.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Place in bowl potatoes, onion and eggs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potato mixture and toss lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nancy's "different" sweet and sour sauce
directions: Drain pear juice into saucepan.
Add sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Add to mixture in saucepan. Stir until thickened.
Slice pears into small pieces and add.

title: pork lo mein
directions: Heat wok to 325°.
Add 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, celery, onion, garlic and pork.
Fry 2 minutes, turning until meat is not pink.
Add mushrooms, carrots and water chestnuts and stir-fry until carrots are cooked but still crisp.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together.
Grease cake pan, then put in flour so cake does not stick in pan.
Put mix in pan.
Set oven at 350° and leave in oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook freezer jam
directions: Mix the sugar and strawberries well; let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve the Sure-Jell in the hot water; boil 1 minute. Add this to the crushed berries; stir for 2 minutes.
Put in jars; let stand 24 hours.
Seal and freeze.
You can make berries and peaches just the same way.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut potatoes, onions and carrots up.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Decrease heat to medium.
Cut steak into bite-size pieces and brown in skillet.
Add to mixture of vegetables.
Add seasoning and cook until done.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Cream butter, cheese, then add flour.
Shape into 2 rolls.
Chill, then cut into biscuits. Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry frozen salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze in muffin cups.
Makes 24-30.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook first five items for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 20 minutes.
Add cheese and soup, cook until melted.
(I melt the cheese in the microwave first.)

title: uncooked pickles
directions: Add 1 cup salt to the sliced cucumbers.
Cover with water; let set 3 days.
Drain.
Wash in cold water.
Add the alum; cover with water for 24 hours.
Rinse in cold water 3 times.
Put back in jar.
Cover with vinegar.
Let set 7 days.
Drain vinegar.
Put 3 cups sugar, small bag of spice and 1 teaspoon turmeric.
Let stand 24 hours.
Add 2 more cups of sugar.
On the third day, add 2 more cups sugar.
That makes 7 cups.
Your pickles are done!!!

title: six-cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup.
Combine pineapple chunks, reserved syrup, mandarin orange sections, coconut, marshmallows and cherries with sour cream.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with pecans.

title: butterfinger ice cream(very good)
directions: Put all ingredients in ice cream churn; do not stir.
Freeze. (As it is freezing in the churn, it will mix itself.)

title: biscuits and sausage gravy
directions: Combine baking mix and sugar in a large bowl; add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface, and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch round cutter. Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Split biscuits; serve with gravy.
Makes 9 biscuits.

title: ham, sausage or bacon casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Can be cut in half or doubled with good results.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 6.
Great as main breakfast dish, served with fruit juice or fruit salad.

title: rich rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, pudding mix, raisins and egg in a saucepan.
Stir over medium heat just until mixture comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into bowl or custard cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: fruit drinks
directions: Peel all fruits that have skins.
Remove all seeds and cores. Add all fruits in blender (or if you have a juicer, even better). Once mixed, add sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and crushed ice.
Blend on low speed.
Add water, if needed.
Taste; if too sweet, add lemon juice.
You might want more sugar.
Great for breakfast. Pour in glass.
(If you want, put umbrella with cherry on stick.)

title: mamma's sugar cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make a soft dough, about 5 cups.
Put flour in bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and baking powder.
Put soda in milk.
Add to flour, etc.
Mix with hands. Roll and cut out cookies the size you like.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scots eggs
directions: Peel hard-boiled eggs.
Divide sausage into 8 parts and flatten each into a round.
Lightly coat eggs with flour.
Shape a portion of sausage around each egg to completely enclose.
Roll each in beaten egg and then in bread crumbs, pressing crumbs well into the sausage.
Drop eggs into a muffin tin and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with mustard or Worcestershire sauce.

title: heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Let marshmallows soften in pineapple juice. Beat marshmallows. Pour in pineapple and fruit cocktail. Whip cream and fold into pineapple mixture.

title: soft bread sticks
directions: Sprinkle yeast	in very warm water.
Stir in 1 teaspoon honey. Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix butter, salt, boiling water and remaining honey in large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg in small
cup;
reserve
one
tablespoon.
Stir
remaining egg into butter
mixture.
Stir
in	yeast until blended.
Add two cups flour; gradually
stir
in	enough	flour
to make a soft dough. Do not knead.

title: missy's easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese first, then add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate for 1 hour.
May pour 1 can cherry pie filling on top of pie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in medium bowl and mix with 1/2 pkg Pepperidge Farms Herb stuffing mix.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli by directions on pkg and drain.
Combine all ingredients and mix 1/3 to 1/2 c. stuffing mix in.
Pour into one large or two small
greased casserole dish and put rest of dressing on top. Bake at 350° 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: stew for two
directions: In large casserole dish, place potatoes, carrots, celery, onions and stew beef.
In small mixing bowl, mix soup mix and water.
Pour over vegetables and meat in casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: roast chicken
directions: Wash the chickens and pat dry.
Rub with the salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in a large roasting pan, breast-side up, and brush on all surfaces with 3 tablespoons of the melted butter.
Roll the potatoes in the remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter and place in the pan with the chicken, along with the onions.
Roast at 425° for 25 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 325° and continue roasting 45 to 50 minutes longer or until the leg joint moves easily.
Pour the lemon juice over the chicken and remove the chicken, potatoes and onions to a platter and keep them warm.
Skim the fat from the pan juices.
Add the water and bring to a boil.
Pour into a gravy boat.
Slice the chicken and serves.
Serves 6.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
In a bowl, add shortening, half of the milk, the extracts and 1 egg to sifted flour mixture; beat well.
Add remaining milk and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: daddy's sweet french fries
directions: Slice sweet potatoes like French fries.
Fry in oil.
After frying, roll in powdered sugar.
Serve hot.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salt water until tender but firm.
When cool, alternate carrots, green peppers and onion in a casserole dish.

title: cherry-glazed baked ham
directions: Bake ham.
Thirty minutes before end of baking, remove from oven.
Pour drippings from pan.
Score fat surface lightly in uniform diamond pattern.
Strain pie filling; set cherries aside. Stir together syrup from pie filling, marmalade, sherry flavoring and orange juice.
Pour syrup mixture on ham.
Continue baking 30 minutes longer or until ham is done, basting frequently with glaze.
Garnish ham with reserved cherries.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large pan, cook beef over medium heat. Drain and remove beef from pan. Add celery, onion and garlic to pan. Cook, stirring for four minutes or until soft. Return beef to pan. Add next 8 ingredients; stir until blended. Spoon half of mixture into 8 inch square baking dish. Arrange half of the cheese slices over top. repeat layers. Place tomatoes on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: basil roasted corn
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Place each ear on a piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Brush with olive oil; sprinkle with basil.
Roll foil around corn and twist at each end.
Grill over medium-hot coals (300° to 350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn at 5-minute intervals.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey. Add beaten egg yolks. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and salt. Add alternately with milk, flour and creamed ingredients. Stir in figs, raisins and almonds. Fold in 6 stiff beaten egg whites. Bake in well greased tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: all-american barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover and simmer gently 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 1 quart.

title: sauteed scallops
directions: Clean
scallops and set aside.
Melt 1/2 the butter.
In a pan,
place
scallops
which
have
been seasoned with salt, crushed garlic, pepper and 1/2 of paprika.
Saute on low heat 5 to 10
minutes
until brown.
Remove to side for a while (place on plate).
In
same pan, add balance of butter, paprika, lemon juice and parsley.
Simmer and stir
for
2 minutes.
Pour over scallops and serve.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients, put approximately 2 tablespoons of filling in center of tortilla and fold.
Let chill overnight and slice into bite size pieces (1/4 to 1/2 slices).
Dip in salsa.

title: taco salad
directions: In advance, (night before serving), brown beef; drain well and chill.
Toss in a salad bowl the lettuce, onion and tomatoes. Add the meat, cheese and beans.
Pour on dressing and top with taco chips just prior to serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, slightly beat the eggs.
Stir in the light corn syrup, brown sugar, melted butter (or margarine) and salt. Add the chopped pecans and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on a preheated cookie sheet at 375° until center is set when gently shaken, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy!
Makes one pie.

title: methodist meat loaf
directions: Saute or fry onions until brown.
Add celery.
Pour over this 1 can of tomato soup.
Fry meat until done.
Add to onions, celery and soup.
Cook 1 package macaroni.
Mix all together by turning gently.
Over this pour mushroom soup.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Fold in the sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Cook until the cheese is melted.
Serves 12 people.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, nutmeg, cinnamon and margarine. Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes after coming to a boil; set aside.
Pare and core apples.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening; mix, add milk and blend.
Divide dough into 6 balls.
Roll each ball into a 5 to 6-inch square.
Arrange 1 sliced apple on each square.
Sprinkle generously with additional sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot each with margarine.
Fold corners to center and pinch together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake, serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Beat together the eggs, cream and seasonings.
Layer the pie shell with cheese and bacon.
Pour the egg mixture over this.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce the oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 40 minutes longer.
Cool slightly before cutting into pie-shaped wedges and serving.

title: crispy cheese potatoes
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 425°.
In greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, toss potatoes and salt together; arrange in even layers.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes or until fork-tender.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons. Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In large saucepan, combine all other ingredients.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add fettucini; toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear apart lettuce and start layering ingredients.
Layer in order listed.
Mix 1 pint mayonnaise and 1/4 cup sugar together and pour over salad.
Seal to edges, then refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and cook between low and medium heat. Do not stir.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Then beat slightly after adding vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: orange salad(sugar-free)
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add frozen juice.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add Mandarin oranges and about 1/2 cup cold water. Chill; serve with sour cream on top, if you like.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups.
