Mix cereal, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Put in muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 22 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: slaw
directions: Dump cabbage, pepper (optional), onion (optional) and carrot together in medium size bowl.

Put white vinegar or cider vinegar, sugar, salt and turmeric in saucepan and boil for 2 or 3 minutes. (Celery seed may be boiled with vinegar or it may be placed on bowl with cabbage, whichever you prefer.)
Pour vinegar mix over cabbage mix and stir.
Place in a bowl that you can seal and put in refrigerator.
Best prepared day before.
Will keep for a long time

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove and discard stems.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff mushrooms. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 28.

title: cinnamon pomanders
directions: Spray vegetable oil on mold or cookie cutter.
Mix cinnamon, 1 cup applesauce and oil.
Knead in more applesauce if needed, a little at a time, until mixture is very stiff "clay."
(It should not be sticky.)
For mold, spray lightly (remove any excess with paper towel).
Dust cinnamon into mold and onto fingers and press a piece of "clay" into mold.
Even out back of clay, then tap mold against cutting board or hand.
Peel out clay; place on cookie sheet, then trim any rough edges with sharp knife.
If a hole is needed, use a small straw to cut it.
Bake 1 hour (until firm), then another hour on wire rack.
Drying needs to be slow to prevent cracking.
For cookie cutter, roll out and cut as you would cookies.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine sour cream, cream of mushroom soup, white wine and mushrooms.
Pour over pork chops in a shallow Pyrex. Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt the chocolate in the top pan of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
When chocolate is melted, add 1 tablespoon of hot water and stir thoroughly.
Dip each strawberry in the chocolate 2/3 of the way towards the stem.
Place the berries on a wax paper-lined cookie sheet to cool.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate coffee dessert
directions: Mix Oreos and 1/3 cup butter together and press into an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Slightly soften ice cream. Press on top of crust.
Freeze until firm.
Mix chocolate, 1 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons butter and evaporated milk together and cook in heavy pan until thick.
Then cool.
After sauce cools, spread over frozen ice cream layer and refreeze.
Soften Cool Whip and spread on top of chocolate layer.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refreeze.
Let sit out of freezer a little while before cutting.

title: quick lunch-english muffin pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread each half English muffin with tomato sauce.
Add slices of any combination from above ingredients, ending with cheese on top.
Place on foil in 350 degree oven till hot and cheese melts, approximately 15 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; add water and sugar.
Add carrots, then cover and simmer until carrots are tender, adding water as necessary to prevent sticking.
Remove cover and bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until all liquid has evaporated and carrots are glazed, stirring gently.
Sprinkle with Accent, salt and pepper.

title: prune cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in mixing bowl, then add liquid and prunes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: strawberry cool whip pie
directions: Add jello mix to boiling water and cook 2 minutes.
Mix together cold water and ice to make 3/4 cup and add to jello. Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove remaining ice.
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk.
Add strawberry slices.
Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is very thick and will mold.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Top with strawberries.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Add pineapple, oranges and orange juice to jello.
Pour into 13 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread with lemon pie filing. Cover; cool.
Spread whipped cream over top.
Garnish with cheese.
Flavor improves with overnight chilling.

title: strawberry vanilla pudding dessert
directions: Place cake cubes in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix pudding with milk and add ice cream, mixing well with electric beater.
Pour evenly over cake cubes.
In separate bowl, mix water with gelatin. Add frozen berries and stir until frozen berries melt.
Pour evenly over pudding mixture.
Do not stir.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: good punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill well before serving.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Spread ribs, meaty side up, in a single layer in a large shallow pan.
Brown in 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes; drain off fat.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper, in saucepan; stir smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick and glossy, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over browned ribs; spoon half of sauce over meat.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Turn ribs; cover with rest of sauce and bake for 30 minutes more, or until well done.

title: nature bread stuffing
directions: Combine celery, bread, carrots and parsley in a large bowl. Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add seasonings and stir. Pour over bread mixture and toss lightly.
Add eggs and water and toss again.
Stuff turkey just before roasting.
Sufficient for 11 to 14 pound turkey.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: chinese crab corn soup
directions: Put chicken and pork bone in water.
Add salt and Accent. Cook until meat is done and remove meat.
Add 2 cans regular corn, creamed corn and crab meat.
Add flour to 1/2 cup broth; mix together.
Add to soup.
Add 2 tablespoons oyster sauce, corn oil and a little bit of salt.
Add egg (take off some white of egg and whip) very slowly while stirring soup; when starts to boil, turn off.

title: veggie hot dish
directions: Cook each vegetable separately until just thawed.
Drain. Grease a 9-inch square casserole.
Layer cooked vegetables.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz and spread over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with French fried onions and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend well.
May be eaten immediately but is improved by mellowing in refrigerator for 2 hours.
May use as dip for any fruit but is especially good with apple slices.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cukes and slice thin.
Chop onions and peppers; combine with cukes and salt.
Let stand 3 hours or all night.
Drain.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in butter. Add Pasta Accents and water.
Stir to combine.
Cover; reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil boneless chicken breasts in water with salt and a dash of pepper.
Remove chicken and cut into small bite size pieces.
Mix 1 1/2 cups grated cheese with chicken in a bowl and set aside.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw out bread but don't permit to raise.
Break 1 loaf up in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter, then add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Pour over the bread.
Break the second loaf on top and let raise for 2 1/2 hours.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, take out of pan on plate.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into two greased and floured cake pans or 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool cake 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: chicken casali
directions: Pound chicken until tender.
Combine cheese, pepper and garlic.
Roll up ingredients in chicken.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Brush with butter.
Dust with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° until done (approximately 40 minutes).

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Preheat oven 400 degrees.
Drain asparagus, reserve liquid. Saute green pepper in butter in skillet until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add cream and 1/2 cup asparagus liquid. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add pimento. Arrange asparagus in shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over asparagus; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes, until asparagus is heated and cheese is lightly browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: calico salad
directions: Prepare ahead of time and refrigerate overnight.

title: the peach bowl
directions: In punch bowl (or other glass bowl) make several layers as follows:
peaches, jello, cake, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Delicious, light and beautiful! Serves a crowd!

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Shape into balls using 1/4 cup for each.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into small bite size balls.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Mix in order.
Dip slices of bread or biscuit slices into mix. Fry in oil, turning to brown both sides.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix to desired consistency to coat food. Excellent for deep fried shrimp, mushrooms, zucchini, etc.

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: To brown meat, crumble into a microwave colander.
Add onion. Place colander over 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Cook covered on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once. Remove colander.
Drain casserole and wipe out.
Transfer meat and onion to casserole.
Stir in enchilada sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Gently fold in tortilla wedges and cheese.
Heat uncovered on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture is heated through.
Serves 4.

title: step cake
directions: You can make any kind of cake you like: tube or layer cake.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Squeeze lemon into large saucepan. Put lemon peels into pan also. Add mustard, salt, sugar, vinegar and worcestershire sauce. Stir well. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 - 30 minutes. Let cool, pour over chicken breast and marinate in refrigerator over night.

title: hot sauce
directions: Chop and cook for 45 minutes (boil).

title: zesty party crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, heat margarine in oven until melted. Remove pan from oven. Stir in cheese and seasoning. Add cereal, pretzels and peanuts, stirring until well coated. Bake 20 minutes, stirring occasionally during baking. Cool. Store in tightly covered container. YIELD: 11 cups.

title: party chicken(serves 8)
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish (can use cooking spray).
Cover bottom of dish with chipped beef slices.
Wrap each chicken breast, lengthwise, with a slice of bacon and arrange on top of chipped beef.
Mix sour cream, soup and sherry or wine; pour over chicken. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 275° uncovered 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over pasta or wild rice.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Keeps well for 2 weeks.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crystal's macaroni delight
directions: Cook box of macaroni to package directions.
Drain.
Add butter and milk and cheese.
Drain tuna and combine with macaroni. Stir over low heat until warm.

title: creamy chicken spread
directions: Cream cheese and drained Swanson chicken.
Add other can Underwood chicken.
Roll into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: ritz goodies
directions: Heat Eagle Brand milk and dates until dates are melted, stirring constantly.
Add pecans.
Spread on crackers.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes at 325°.
Watch closely; don't scorch.
Cool.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo; add sugar and vanilla.
Add milk, if necessary, to spread.
Spread glaze over cooled crackers.
Dry.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Mix all ingredients, heat and serve in sandwiches.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Start with 7 ounces each, any pasta.

title: best ever fudge brownies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in medium saucepan. Before completely melted add cocoa. Mix in 1 stick of butter. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir well to smooth consistency. Add flour, walnuts and chocolate chips. Stir and blend well. Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna 1
directions: Saute meat.
Add garlic and saute; then add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer in a large pot about 30 minutes.

title: beef pot roast with cornbread dumplings
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Brown.
Add water, tomato sauce, onions and garlic. Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to meat and continue cooking until tender (about 1 hour).

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix Italian dressing with melted margarine.
Roll chicken in mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: bouja
directions: Boil slowly for 24 to 30 hours.

title: bing cherry congealed salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple; set aside (add water to get 2 cups).
Bring juice to a boil and add Jell-O; cool.
Add Coke and stir.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold rinsed with cold water; refrigerate until firm.
Serve with mayonnaise or sour cream.
Serves 12.

title: buckeyes recipe
directions: With a hand-held electric mixer, beat peanut butter, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar and flour until well blended.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls; place on wax paper lined cookie sheet and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Melt chocolate chips; one at a time, spearing balls with toothpick and dip ball into the chocolate to cover most of it.
Place chocolate side down on cookie sheet, smoothing over or filling in toothpick gaps with more chocolate, if necessary.
Refrigerate buckeyes for about 15 minutes longer or until the chocolate is set.
Store buckeyes tightly covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 dozen buckeyes candies.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook first 3 items until meat is brown.
Add other ingredients in order.
Cover and turn heat to low cook 45 minutes.
Do not lift cover after heat is turned down.
This is best cooked in iron skillet or heavy pan.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in an ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix, eggs and cherry pie filling together. Bake at 350° for 27 to 35 minutes until done.

title: homemade hot cakes
directions: Mix in all ingredients together until all blended together evenly. Heat frying pan well with 1 teaspoon of oil or cooking spray evenly. Put about a cup of mixture in pan and let bubbles form all over. Flip with spatula to other side and cook until brown on both sides. Makes approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: crawfish elegant
directions: In skillet, saute crawfish in 1/2 stick oleo for 10 minutes. In another skillet, saute green onions and parsley in 1 stick oleo. Blend in flour and gradually half and half, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add sherry and crawfish being careful not to add fat in bottom of pan.
Season to taste.
Serve in patty shells, over rice or pasta.
Freezes well.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix in crushed vanilla wafers and baking powder.
Add pecans and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Use a 10 inch iron skillet.
Cook the hamburger and onion over medium heat.
Break the meat up into small pieces with fork and drain.
While meat is frying, combine milk, biscuit mix, eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix well with whisk until smooth. When meat is done, pour the batter over it in the hot skillet. Sprinkle
with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until done. Remove from oven, cut into 8 wedges. Serve.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add beaten egg whites by folding them in carefully.
Sprinkle top of pie with cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, then finish baking at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup and water to boil; add cheese and gelatin (which has been dissolved in a little water).
Whip together and cool. Add shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: mushroom and onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart shallow baking dish. Saute onions and mushrooms in oil until tender.
Set aside.
In blender, process cottage cheese until almost smooth.
Add sour cream, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Process until combined.
Stir in onions and mushrooms.
Pour into dish and bake 40 minutes or until set.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shoestring potatoes, and refrigerate.
Add shoestring potatoes just before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry-raspberry spinach salad
directions: In blender, process raspberries until smooth.
Strain through a sieve.
Discard seeds.

title: hearty potato-ham chowder
directions: Peel and dice the potatoes. In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add potatoes, 2 cups water and seasonings. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Make a paste of the flour and 1/3 cup water. Add the paste to the potato mixture, stirring constantly to make smooth. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Stir in drained corn and diced ham. Heat thoroughly. Garnish with chopped parsley just before serving. Serves 6.

title: durkee 15 minute casserole
directions: Line bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan with Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks. Place beef, 1/2 of Durkee onions, broccoli and tomato in Tater Tot shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer until cheese melts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in beans. Layer with cheese, mushroom soup and eggs.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roast pork wraps with cranberry mustard
directions: 1. Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or baking sheet.

title: taco pasta
directions: Cook beef, add cream cheese, salt and chili powder and simmer. Toss shells with butter, fill with beef mixture.
Arrange in buttered pan.
Pour sauce over each shell.
Cover with foil, bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover, top with cheeses and chips, bake 15 minutes more, until bubbly.
Top with sour cream and onions. May be garnished with lettuce, black olives and tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fiesta barley salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: easy sauerbraten
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Cook slow 6 to 8 hours.
Remove meat; slice.
Put gravy through food mill.
Put meat back into gravy.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount boiling water until just tender (about 5 minutes).
Drain.
Combine celery, almonds, chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add broth and half and half.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over celery.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Top with melted butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together.
Add sauces and simmer.
Cook noodles as directed on bag.
Layer in crock-pot the ground beef mixture, noodles, cheeses and pepperoni until full.
Cook on low until cheese melts.

title: italian seasoned bread crumbs
directions: Bread Crumbs:
Save slices from each loaf and keep in freezer until you have about a loaf.
Mix all ingredients together well and store in airtight container.
Use for meat coating, topping on casseroles, etc.
Very good on cube steaks and pork chops.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion in margarine. Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento, salt, pepper and half of the cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: rolls
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool until lukewarm, then add yeast.
Add enough flour to stir like cake batter.
Put in warm place and let rise for 2 hours. Work in approximately 2 quarts of flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Store this in a large container until ready to use. Yields approximately 60 rolls.

title: tender ribs
directions: Parboil ribs in water with bay leaf and garlic; allow to cool. Combine in large saucepan the remaining ingredients.
"Cook down" sauce for 30 minutes.
Baste ribs generously.
Grill meat side down 10 minutes; turn and grill 10 minutes longer.

title: six week muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran and mix together.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store covered in the refrigerator and use as desired.
Batter will
keep for 6 weeks.
Grease muffin cups and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Over hot (not boiling) water, melt the butterscotch morsels and butter or margarine.
Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar.
Cool 5 minutes, blending eggs and vanilla. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in ungreased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: quick chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a simmer.
Mix in cooked, chopped chicken and vegetables.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place biscuits evenly over top of mixture and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole with rice
directions: Bake chicken breast in oven until tender and light brown.
Mix soup with water and pour over chicken.
Bake for 10 more minutes or until soup is hot.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Serve chicken with Rice-A-Roni.
Bake chicken in 350° oven.

title: baked corn(eastern shore of virginia)
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and milk.
Add corn to mixture.
Melt margarine in oblong baking dish.
Pour mixture over margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, water and juice, 3 cups boiling water and jello and sugar.
Grind cranberries, orange, apples and celery and combine to mixture.
Put in large mold and refrigerate.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, cornflakes, applesauce, onion, salt and pepper. Roll in balls.
Place in pan.
Mix water, catsup and sauce.
Pour over balls and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered or you can place in an electric skillet.
Pour sauce over and fry until brown.

title: italian meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, add onions and saute until onions are limp. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Yields 6 (2/3 cup) servings. Each 2/3 cup contains approximately (exchanges):
2 meat, 1 vegetable.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Slice strawberries and place on paper towels to drain. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and cream cheese until smooth, and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping, blending well.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto lightly greased pizza pan.
(Be sure to use a pizza pan with 1/2-inch raised edge.)
In skillet, brown sausage, then drain.
Add hash browns; spread over dough. Beat eggs with milk; pour over sausage mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: crock-pot rice pudding
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; pour into preheated crock-pot (high).
Lower crock-pot to the low setting and let cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Combine eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to milk and rice mixture and cook another 1/2 hour or longer as needed.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Whip cottage cheese in blender.
Stir in pickle, salad dressing, onions, garlic salt and milk if desired.
Serve with raw vegetables or a relish tray.
Also good with chips.

title: claire's chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Mix equal amounts of crumbs and grated cheese; dredge chicken in mixture until evenly coated. Bake at 250° for 2 hours or at 350° for 1 hour.
Very moist and tender.

title: mandarin orange and cashew chicken
directions: Drain mandarin oranges; reserve 2 tablespoons syrup.
Blend reserved syrup and stir-fry sauce.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken, cashews and garlic.
Stir-fry 3 minutes; remove.
Heat remaining oil in same pan.
Add onion and snow peas; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add chicken mixture and stir-fry sauce mixture to onion-snow peas mixture; cook and stir to coat all ingredients with sauce.
Remove from heat; stir in oranges.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients except 8 ounces of cheese.
Layer macaroni and sauce; top with remaining cheese.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter until melted. Cool.

title: beer batter
directions: Sift together flour, salt and pepper.
Make well in the center and pour in beer and oil in a stream, stirring while doing so. Stir until smooth.

title: mallow-whipt and sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, margarine, orange juice and salt. Whip in 1 cup marshmallows.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with additional marshmallows; return to oven until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef until brown. Drain. Then add all of the ingredients and cook about 1 hour.

title: good fried chicken
directions: Combine salt, pepper, paprika and flour.
Add chicken and coat 2 to 3 pieces at a time.
Heat margarine and Crisco in an electric skillet or cast-iron skillet
until a drop of water sizzles in it. Brown meaty chicken first, then add remaining pieces.
When lightly browned, reduce heat and add 2 tablespoons of water. Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture,
beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake a 350° oven for 1 hour.
If baked in layers, bake only for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf (8 x 4 inches) or 2 (9 inch) layers.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix orange jello and hot water.
Add frozen orange juice, pineapple with juice and drained mandarin oranges.
Chill until set.

title: low-fat soup
directions: Brown meat over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer to plate and set aside.
Add oil in saucepan along with vegetables.
Cook until soft.
Stir in flour; stir 1 more minute.
Gradually add beef broth, tomatoes with juice, water, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Stir in ground turkey.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup frozen green peas; cook 5 minutes more.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Marshmallow Creme together.
Layer with strawberries.
Keep chilled. Can be used as a fruit dip.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Crush cookies; press into bottom of pan.
Mix pudding.
Add 4 crushed candy bars to pudding; pour over cookies.
Put in refrigerator; chill 1 hour. Spread Cool Whip over pudding; top with last 2 crushed candy bars.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Boil chicken until tender, cool and remove from bones.
Cut chicken into small pieces.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage in large skillet, add water, oil, salt, and slice of ham (country ham is very good).
Turn burner on medium and let cook until all the water has evaporated, then let simmer for about 5 minutes (very good).

title: easy hot fudge dessert
directions: Mix biscuit mix, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla until well blended.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/2 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour hot water over all.

title: humdingers
directions: Melt butter and sugar together.
Add chopped dates.
Cook 5 - 8 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts, Rice Krispies and mix well.
Roll into small balls and coat with powdered sugar.
Makes 50 small balls.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Serve as dip for fresh vegetables.

title: company eggs
directions: Cube bread.
Place bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese to top of bread.
Beat eggs well and add to eggs; milk, salt, dry mustard and pepper, mix.
Pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 325° to 350° oven.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Mix according to directions on cake box.
Pour into greased pan.
Pour over mixture butterscotch chops and chopped nuts.

title: belgian broccoli
directions: Cook fresh broccoli until tender or thaw 2 packages of frozen broccoli.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil; brown broccoli in oil with onion, parsley flakes, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and cook until liquid reduces, about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: red french dressing
directions: Add all ingredients in food processor and mix well. Refrigerate until used up.

title: jimmy's harborside snow crab salad
directions: Drain crabmeat of natural juices.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve chilled on a bed of lettuce and tomato or in rolls.

title: severn layer casserole
directions: Using a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, layer rice (uncooked) and corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Then layer tomato sauce, parsley, onion, green pepper and ground beef and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover meat with 4 strips of bacon, cut in half.
Cover dish and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: porcupine meat balls and veggies
directions: Combine beef, egg, salt, rice and 1/2 of soup mix. Mix well. Form into golf ball size balls.
Mix soups and water.
Pour in oven bag.
Add vegetables and meatballs in 1/2 soup mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Depends on the size you cut them.

title: cheese butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into small butter molds or shape butter into a cylinder.
Chill until firm.
Serve with rolls or use on vegetables.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the mushroom soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
Firmly shape meat mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons drippings; reserve.

title: tasty rice dish
directions: Do not drain mushrooms.
Put all ingredients in casserole baking dish. Mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Stir once after baking 1/2 hour.

title: chow chow
directions: Put each vegetable into separate bowl and sprinkle a small amount of salt over each.
Let stand 4 hours.
Press juice from each vegtetable and combine together with dry ingredients.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour in 1 cup milk, stirring constantly.
Add more milk until desired thickness.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: skillet cookies(from the files of charlie mae williams)
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, dates and egg yolks in skillet. Cook 10 minutes over low heat, mashing dates as you stir.
Turn off heat; add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
When cool enough to handle, roll in coconut.
Roll in long roll about 1 1/2-inch thick.
Can also be rolled into balls about 1-inch.
Wrap roll in waxed paper or store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Takes about 8 hours to ripen.

title: swedish limpa bread
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar and let sit for 5 minutes.
Add rye flour to yeast mixture, then seed mixture, then white or unbleached flour.
Mix.
Turn out on board; let rest for 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic; let rise in greased, covered bowl until double in size.
Punch down; divide into 2 parts.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until loaves are done.

title: tasty pineapple sherbet(low calorie)
directions: Soften gelatin in 2 tablespoons cold water.
Dissolve over hot water.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, pineapple and vanilla.
Add gelatin.
Fold in egg white.
Turn into refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm, stirring once.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: raisin spice bars
directions: Boil raisins for 13 minutes, covered with water.
Drain water, then add 1 cup water and boil 3 more minutes.
Drain and add enough water to make one cup. Mix all ingredients except the raisins and water, then add the raisins and water.
Stir until completely mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Put chicken, pineapple, celery, oranges, olives, peppers and onion in bowl.
Stir together mayonnaise and mustard and pour over all other ingredients and carefully fold until well blended. Cover and chill for several hours.
Just before serving, add the chow mein noodles.

title: hummos(low-fat - tahini-free)
directions: Puree all ingredients together and spread on plate to serve. Garnish with olive oil, paprika, cumin, minced parsley, and black olives.
Serve with pita bread.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat with mixer.
Add 1/4 cup nuts.
Put in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until done, like custard pie.

title: belgium salad(must chill for 24 hours before serving.)
directions: Drain green beans, corn and peas and mix together.
Chop celery, onion, green pepper and pimento and mix.
Combine first two mixtures.
Mix and bring to a boil sugar, oil, salt, vinegar, pepper.
Combine all ingredients together cover and chill 24 hours.

title: pesto pasta with pine nuts*
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve on hot cooked pasta of your choice.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion, garlic, red pepper, and celery.
Stir in chili powder and cumin; cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, breaking them up with a spoon, stir in beans and corn.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Return to a full boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 - 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Add bacon strips to top, if desired.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter and cheese with pastry blender or forks; stir in sour cream.
Shape into a ball and chill 2 hours.
On lightly floured board, roll out dough 1/8 inch thick. Cut into strips, 3 x 1/4-inch.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: yogurt cucumber sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, green onion, curry powder, salt, mustard, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in cucumber.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and soda into buttermilk at room temperature. Mix as for biscuits (add all ingredients).
Roll dough thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Roll in flour.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add chocolate.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Turn into two 9-inch pans lined on bottom with wax paper.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 30 minutes.
Spread with chocolate frosting.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Simmer chicken breast in water until tender.
Remove and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Simmer carrot strips separately in a little water for about 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, catsup, cornstarch, vinegar, salt and soy sauce into a smooth paste.
Stir into chicken broth, cooking until thickened.
Add drained pineapple chunks, onions, carrots, chicken and green pepper.
Heat together 5 or 10 minutes on very low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: oriental salad
directions: In a bowl,
place
chopped
cabbage, chopped scallions, browned sesame seed and
browned
almonds.	Break noodles from soup package and add these.
Take season package from soup and add oil, sugar and
vinegar.
Mix
separately
and
pour
over salad and toss.
You can add
as many seeds and almonds as you would like.
Sunflower seeds are good in it too.

title: microwaved caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in a large paper bag.
Place the rest of the ingredients in a large microwave safe bowl.
Boil for 2 minutes (approximatley 4 minutes in the microwave depending on butter and microwave.)
Add 1/2 tsp. baking soda.
Stir and pour over popcorn in the paper bag. Microwave (in bag) for 1
1/2 minutes on full power.
Stir. Microwave for another 1
1/2 minutes on full power.
Take out of microwave and stir in bag.
Spread on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water; cook to soft ball stage (236°). Add peanuts and melted butter; continue cooking until syrup is a golden brown (290°). Scorches easily! Stir during last few minutes of cooking. Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla. Stir until mixture thickens. Pour into buttered tins and break into pieces when cold. If roasted peanuts are used, add to syrup before removing from heat.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly.
When steam shows, remove from heat and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Put crackers in bottom of large glass oblong dish.
Mix in melted butter.
Mix pudding and milk.
Mix in ice cream.
Pour on top of cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 3 or 4 crushed crackers.
Freeze for about 1 hour.

title: no cook diabetic cookies
directions: Cook margarine, milk and unsweetened chocolate together for 1 minute.
Stir while cooking.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pat out mixture in small patties.
Do not bake.
May be frozen.
Large batch.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Crush Doritos into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together, except Western dressing and taco mix. Pour 1/2 bottle Western dressing over all; mix thoroughly.
Add taco mix with other half bottle of dressing; shake well.
Pour remaining dressing over salad; mix again.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon juice.
Mix lemon juice in last.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: fullabull's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with pecans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in small amount
of boiling water until tender.
Do not overcook.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add all at once to the milk and stir until it thickens.
Sauce should be real thick.
Combine sauce with the zucchini.
Place in casserole and top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend well the first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls about the size of a thumb.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Put toothpick in the ball and dip into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until hard.
Makes 125.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: In bowl, mix noodles, cucumbers, tomatoes, onions, parsley, chicken and dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serves 5.

title: tang pie
directions: Using a spoon, mix Eagle Brand milk, sugar and Tang in a mixing bowl.
Pour into pie crust; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip or alone.

title: easiest cheesecake ever
directions: In a bowl combine cream cheese, sugar and milk using a hand mixer.
Mix in candy bits, then fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze for about 4 hours.
Sprinkle with saved candy bits before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a bowl.
Add scallops; cover and chill.
Spoon scallop mixture into 4 individual baking shells. Place shells on a baking sheet.
Broil 2 inches from heat for 3 minutes; stir and broil 2 minutes.
Combine butter and breadcrumbs; sprinkle over scallops and broil 1 minute or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Cook fresh tomato and onion 20 minutes (if canned, 10 minutes).
Process tomato and onion.
Put in blender through sieve or food processor.
Cool.
Blend sugar and flour into melted margarine.
Gradually add tomato.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Gradually blend in scalded milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Do not boil.
If it curdles, put in blender.

title: instant cheese sauce
directions: Combine milk and soup in pan; mix well. Cover and heat thoroughly. Do not let boil. Serve over meat loaf, hamburgers or chicken.

title: southern baked rabbit
directions: Clean rabbits, then cut in pieces at joints.
Cover with cold water.
Add vinegar and let stand overnight.
Drain and dry well. Rub with salt, pepper and butter.
Place in baking pan in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: skillet breakfast
directions: Place potatoes and turkey bacon in skillet (nonstick).
Cover and cook over medium heat, about 12 minutes, stirring often until potatoes are fork-tender.
Stir in onion and chili powder.
Pour eggs over and cover.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes or until set.
Cut and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo in microwave or on top of stove, using large bowl or pan.
Remove from stove or oven.
Add the peanut butter and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Add powdered sugar; mix.
Put in ungreased square pan or dish.
Cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: clam chowder(can do ahead)
directions: Fry bacon in a heavy skillet until crisp.
Pour off drippings, leaving enough to saute the onion.
Add celery, carrots, garlic and potatoes.
Add two cups of water (more if needed, enough to cover the potatoes), salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and bacon. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken or turkey enchiladas
directions: Layer the ingredients in large rectangle baking dish: tortillas, chicken/turkey mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let sit at least 10 minutes before serving.
Best to bake the night before serving.

title: mozzarella eggs
directions: Heat butter in a skillet until melted.
Break eggs into skillet one at a time, carefully.
Cook over medium heat until whites are set.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour water into a skillet; place slices of cheese over eggs.
Sprinkle with oregano and paprika.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: sausage and bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: scotch trifle for busy people
directions: Cut up pound cake and layer it in bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle with sherry until absorbed.
Drain very well the fruit cocktail and spread over cake.
Cover with vanilla pudding.
Whip the cream and sweeten with 2 to 4 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread over vanilla pudding.

title: mushroom delite
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add chopped garlic.
Take stems out of the mushrooms and put the cheese in its place, by breaking it up into small pieces.
Add mushrooms to butter-cheese side up.
Cover and cook about 8 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: microwave peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir in peanuts.
Microwave for three to five minutes, or until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Microwave on High one to two minutes, or more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie pan.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
In baking dish, mix remaining ingredients.
Lay bacon on top in crisscross fashion.
Bake in 350° oven until onions are done.
Great with barbecue!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 3 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, in pan and cook until smooth.
Add butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: finger jello
directions: Boil water.
Stir in unflavored gelatin until dissolved.
Then stir in jello until dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour in cake pan of choice (the smaller the pan the thicker the jello). Refrigerate until set.

title: small chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
If desired, sprinkle grated cheese on top as dish is removed from oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, buttermilk, soda, bananas, vanilla and flour.
When all mixed, add nuts last.
Bake in 2 loaf pans that have been oiled and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
